attacks.text: Discard all of your opponent's Pokémon Tool cards and Stadium cards in play. If you do, prevent all effects, including damage, done to Electivire during your opponent's next turn.

name: Lucario LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Lucario. Lucario LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Stance
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Lucario LV.X from your hand onto your Active Lucario, you may use this power. Prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Lucario during your opponent's next turn. (If Lucario is no longer your Active Pokémon, this effect ends.)

attacks.name: Close Combat
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Lucario by attacks is increased by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Magmortar LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Magmortar. Magmortar LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Torrid Wave
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Magmortar is your Active Pokémon, you may choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon. That Pokémon is now Burned. Put 3 damage counters instead of 2 on that Pokémon between turns. This power can't be used if Magmortar is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Flame Bluster
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to Magmortar. Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 100 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) During your next turn, Magmortar can't use Flame Bluster.

name: Time-Space Distortion
rules: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, search your discard pile for a Pokémon, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand.

name: Ampharos

abilities.name: Jamming
abilities.text: After your opponent plays a Supporter card from his or her hand, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon. You can't use more than 1 Jamming Poké-Body each turn.

attacks.name: Cluster Bolt
attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy attached to Ampharos. If you do, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any Energy cards attached to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: The tip of its tail shines brightly. In the olden days, people sent signals using the tail's light.

name: Blastoise

abilities.name: Waterlog
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach as many basic Water Energy cards from your hand to any of your Pokémon in any way you like. If you do, your turn ends. This power can't be used if Blastoise is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: Does 50 damage plus 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 40 damage in this way.

flavorText: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.

name: Charizard

abilities.name: Fury Blaze
abilities.text: If your opponent has 3 or less Prize cards left, each of Charizard's attacks does 50 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Blast Burn
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard. If tails, discard 4 Energy cards attached to Charizard. (If you can't, this attack does nothing.)

flavorText: It is said that CHARIZARD's fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.

name: Entei

abilities.name: Burning Coat
abilities.text: Whenever 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from Entei's attacks, discard the top 3 cards from your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Blaze Roar
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Flip a coin. If tails, discard 2 Fire Energy attached to Entei.

flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

name: Flygon

abilities.name: Irritating Buzz
abilities.text: As long as Flygon is your Active Pokémon, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Active Pokémon between turns, excluding Fighting Pokémon.

attacks.name: Sand Sonic
attacks.text: If you attach a Fighting Energy card from your hand to Flygon during this turn, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as "The Desert Spirit."

name: Gallade

attacks.name: Sonic Blade
attacks.text: Put damage counters on the Defending Pokémon until it is 50 HP away from being Knocked Out. If you do, your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psychic Cut
attacks.text: You may choose as many of your face-down Prize cards as you like and put them face up. If you do, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage for each Prize card you chose. (These cards remain face up for the rest of the game.)

flavorText: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

name: Gardevoir

abilities.name: Telepass
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your opponent's discard pile for a Supporter card and use the effect of that card as the effect of this power. (The Supporter card remains in your opponent's discard pile.) You can't use more than 1 Telepass Poké-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Gardevoir is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Psychic Lock
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, your opponent can't use any Poké-Powers on his or her Pokémon.

flavorText: It will try to guard its trusted Trainer with its life. It has the ability to see the future.

name: Gastrodon East Sea

abilities.name: Osmotic Pressure
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Gastrodon West Sea in play, you may move up to 3 damage counters from Gastrodon East Sea to 1 of your Gastrodon West Sea.

attacks.name: Dwindling Wave
attacks.text: Does 80 damage minus 10 damage for each damage counter on Gastrodon East Sea.

flavorText: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.

name: Gastrodon West Sea

attacks.name: Raging Flood
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Gastrodon West Sea. Then, remove 2 damage counters from Gastrodon West Sea.

attacks.name: Wild Waves
attacks.text: Put 1 damage counter on each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

flavorText: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.

name: Ho-Oh

abilities.name: Phoenix Turn
abilities.text: Once during your opponent's turn, if Ho-Oh would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, you may flip a coin. If heads, Ho-Oh isn't discarded. Instead, remove all damage counters, Special Conditions, and other effects from Ho-Oh. Then, discard all cards attached to Ho-Oh (except for Energy cards). This counts as Ho-Oh being Knocked Out and your opponent takes a Prize card.

attacks.name: Rainbow Wing
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage times the number of different types of basic Energy cards attached to Ho-Oh.

flavorText: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.

name: Jumpluff

abilities.name: Cotton Spore
abilities.text: Whenever Jumpluff would be damaged by your opponent's attack, flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Jumpluff by that attack.

attacks.name: Cottonweed Punch
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. For each heads, this attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

name: Lickilicky

attacks.name: Tongue Reel
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If you choose a Benched Pokémon, switch the Defending Pokémon with that Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to the Pokémon you chose. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Boundless Power
attacks.text: During your next turn, Lickilicky can't attack.

flavorText: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting to close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

name: Ludicolo

abilities.name: Rain Dish
abilities.text: At any time between turns, remove 1 damage counter from Ludicolo.

attacks.name: Nature Power
attacks.text: If you have a Stadium Card in play, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage. If your opponent has a Stadium card in play, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can't help breaking out into a dance.

name: Lugia

attacks.name: Silver Wing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon and return it to your opponent's hand.

attacks.name: Psychic Destruction
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon has any Energy cards attached to it, this attack's base damage is 40 instead of 120.

flavorText: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.

name: Mew

attacks.name: Psychic Balance
attacks.text: If you have less cards in your hand than your opponent, draw cards until you have the same number of cards as your opponent. (If you have more or the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does nothing.)

attacks.name: Re-creation
attacks.text: Choose an attack on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon in his or her discard pile. Re-creation copies that attack except for its Energy cost. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.) Mew performs that attack.

flavorText: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe MEW to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

name: Raikou

abilities.name: Thunder Rumble
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you attach a Lightning Energy card from your hand to Raikou, you may put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Thunder Climb
attacks.text: Discard 3 cards from the top of your deck. This attack does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each Lightning Energy card you discarded. Then, attach those Lightning Energy cards to 1 of your Pokémon.

flavorText: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.

name: Roserade

attacks.name: Sleep Poison
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Magical Leaf
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage and remove 3 damage counters from Roserade.

flavorText: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.

name: Salamence

attacks.name: Direct Hit
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dragon Finish
attacks.text: Discard 2 basic Fire Energy cards or 2 basic Water Energy cards attached to Salamence. If you discarded 2 basic Fire Energy cards, this attack does 100 damage to the Defending Pokémon. If you discarded 2 Basic Water Energy cards, this attack does 100 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) (If you can't discard cards, this attack does nothing.)

flavorText: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changes, and wings grew out.

name: Suicune

abilities.name: Aqua Recover
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Suicune from your hand onto your Bench, you may search your discard pile for up to 3 Water Pokémon, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand.

attacks.name: Cure Stream
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

name: Venusaur

abilities.name: Miracle Aroma
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, choose either Asleep, Burned, or Poisoned. The Defending Pokémon is now affected by that Special Condition. This power can't be used if Venusaur is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Giant Bloom
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove 4 damage counters from Venusaur.

flavorText: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.

name: Absol

attacks.name: Baleful Wind
attacks.text: Choose a card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it. If you discarded a Trainer, Supporter, or Stadium card, choose 1 more card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

attacks.name: Raid
attacks.text: If you played Absol from your hand during this turn, this attack's base damage is 40 instead of 10.

flavorText: It senses disasters coming and appears before people only to warn them of impending danger.

name: Arcanine

abilities.name: Flame Dash
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play Arcanine from your hand to evolve 1 of your Benched Pokémon, you may switch Arcanine with 1 of your Active Pokémon. If you do, you may move any number of Energy cards attached to that Pokémon to Arcanine.

attacks.name: Inferno Onrush
attacks.text: Arcanine does 40 damage to itself.

flavorText: Its proud and regal appearance has captured the hearts of people since long ago.

name: Banette

attacks.name: Ghost Head
attacks.text: Put as many damage counters as you like on Banette. (You can't put more than Banette's remaining HP.) Put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spiteful Pain
attacks.text: If Banette is in your discard pile, this attack does 40 damage plus 40 more damage, then search your discard pile for Banette, show it to your opponent, and shuffle it into your deck.

flavorText: A doll that became a Pokémon over its grudge from being junked. It seeks the child that disowned it.

name: Dugtrio

attacks.name: Dig Trap
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Dugtrio during your opponent's next turn. If Dugtrio is your Active Pokémon at the end of your opponent's next turn, put 6 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Pit Trap
attacks.text: Your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this attack does 50 damage plus 50 more damage.

flavorText: Its three heads moves alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles.

name: Electivire

abilities.name: Motor Drive
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your discard pile for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to Electivire. This power can't be used if Electivire is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Discharge
attacks.text: Discard all Lightning Energy attached to Electivire. Flip a coin for each Lightning Energy you discarded. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

name: Electrode

abilities.name: Energy Shift
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if Electrode would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, you may use this power. Electrode isn't discarded. Instead, attach it as an Energy card to 1 of your Pokémon. While attached, this card is a Special Energy card and provides every type of Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time. (Has no effect other than providing Energy.)

attacks.name: Ion Blast
attacks.text: You may do 40 damage plus 60 more damage. If you do, Electrode does 100 damage to itself.

flavorText: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.

name: Furret

attacks.name: Keen Eye
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Baton Pass
attacks.text: You may switch Furret with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, move as many Energy cards attached to Furret as you like to the new Active Pokémon.

flavorText: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.

name: Golduck

attacks.name: Encore
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can use only that attack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Break Beam
attacks.text: You may do 40 damage plus 20 more damage. If you do, Golduck is now Confused.

flavorText: A Pokémon that lives in lakes. It swims faster than any human swimming champion.

name: Golem

attacks.name: Double Throw
attacks.text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to each of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Megaton Rock
attacks.text: You may do 40 damage instead of 80 to the Defending Pokémon. If you do, during your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Golem by attacks is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: It sheds its hide once a year. Its boulderlike body is so tough, even dynamite can't harm it.

name: Jynx

attacks.name: Icy Kiss
attacks.text: If Jynx was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Lovely Kiss
attacks.text: Move 2 damage counters from Jynx to the Defending Pokémon. If Smoochum is anywhere under Jynx, move 4 damage counters instead.

flavorText: It cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.

name: Magmortar

abilities.name: Flame Body
abilities.text: When you attach a Fire Energy card from your hand to Magmortar, remove 2 damage counters from Magmortar.

attacks.name: Flame Blast
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the number of Fire Energy attached to Magmortar.

attacks.name: Fireball Bazooka
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

name: Minun

abilities.name: Minus Charge
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if any Pokémon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn, you may draw 2 cards. You can't use more than 1 Minus Charge Poké-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Minun is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Tag Play —
attacks.text: If you have Plusle on your Bench, you may move an Energy card attached to Minun to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

name: Mothim

attacks.name: Silver Wind
attacks.text: During your next turn, if an attack does damage to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 40 more damage.

attacks.name: Raging Scales
attacks.text: If Mothim has any damage counters on it, this attack does 30 damage plus 40 more damage.

flavorText: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.

name: Nidoking

attacks.name: Poison Rub
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. Before doing damage, you may switch 1 of the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. The new Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Pride Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Nidoqueen on your Bench. This attack does 60 damage plus 30 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

name: Pidgeot

attacks.name: Mirror Move
attacks.text: If Pidgeot was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does the same amount of damage done to Pidgeot to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: By flapping its wings with all its might, PIDGEOT can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.

name: Plusle

abilities.name: Plus Charge
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn, you may search your discard pile for up to 2 basic Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. You can't use more than 1 Plus Charge Poké-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Plusle is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Tag Play +
attacks.text: If you have Minun on your Bench, you may do 20 damage to any 1 Benched Pokémon instead. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

name: Sharpedo

abilities.name: Rough Skin
abilities.text: If Sharpedo is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Sharpedo is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Strike Wound
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon has 2 or more damage counters on it, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage. This attack damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

flavorText: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as "The Bully of the Sea."

name: Sunflora

abilities.name: Grass Whistle
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 1 damage counter from each of your Grass Pokémon. You can't use more than 1 Grass Whistle Poké-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Sunflora is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Petal Dance
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads. If you get 2 or more heads, Sunflora is now Confused.

flavorText: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

name: Unown [S]

abilities.name: Set
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown S, Unown E, and Unown T on your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for an Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it on top of your deck.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: Weavile

abilities.name: Dark Engage
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Each of your Active Pokémon's type is Darkness until the end of your turn. If that Pokémon is no longer your Active Pokémon, this effect ends.

attacks.name: Shadow Charge
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Darkness Energy cards and attach them to any of your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Chip Off
attacks.text: If your opponent has 6 or more cards in his or her hand, discard a number of cards without looking until your opponent has 5 cards left in his or her hand.

flavorText: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

name: Wormadam Plant Cloak

abilities.name: Plant Cloak
abilities.text: If Wormadam Plant Cloak has 2 or more Grass Energy attached to it, Wormadam Plant Cloak gets +40 HP.

attacks.name: Leaf Hurricane
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon has fewer remaining HP than Wormadam Plant Cloak, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

name: Wormadam Sandy Cloak

abilities.name: Sandy Cloak
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, excluding damage, done to Wormadam Sandy Cloak.

attacks.name: Push Over
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 damage for each Fighting Energy attached to Wormadam Sandy Cloak.

flavorText: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

name: Wormadam Trash Cloak

abilities.name: Trash Cloak
abilities.text: If Wormadam Trash Cloak has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, any damage done to Wormadam Trash Cloak by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Iron Tackle
attacks.text: Wormadam Trash Cloak does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

name: Xatu

abilities.name: Psychic Shift
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if Xatu is on your Bench, you may choose 1 Special Condition from 1 of your Active Pokémon and remove that Special Condition. Then, 1 of the Defending Pokémon is now affected by that Special Condition that you chose.

attacks.name: Energy Singe
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.

name: Breloom

attacks.name: Drain Punch
attacks.text: Remove from Breloom a number of damage counters equal to the amount of Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Homing Uppercut
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon's Retreat Cost is 0, this attack does 60 damage plus 60 more damage.

flavorText: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.

name: Charmeleon

attacks.name: Fire Fang
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Flare Tail
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a Fire Energy attached to Charmeleon and this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: In the rocky mountains where CHARMELEON live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.

name: Cloyster

attacks.name: Withdraw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Cloyster by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Spine Missile
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. For each heads, choose an opponent's Pokémon in play and this attack does 20 damage to those Pokémon. (You may choose the same Pokémon more than once.) (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.

name: Donphan

attacks.name: Rapid Spin
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon, if any. You switch Donphan with 1 of your Benched Pokémon, if any.

attacks.name: Bash In
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 70 damage plus 60 more damage.

flavorText: It attacks by curling up, then rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.

name: Farfetch'd

attacks.name: Swords Dance
attacks.text: During your next turn, Farfetch'd's Leek Slap attack's base damage is 60.

attacks.name: Leek Slap
attacks.text: During your next turn, Farfetch'd can't use Leek Slap.

flavorText: It can't live without the stalk it holds. That's why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

name: Flaaffy

attacks.name: Attract Current
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Electromagnetic Kick
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Flaaffy does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.

name: Ivysaur

attacks.name: Leech Seed
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from Ivysaur.

flavorText: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower's coming bloom.

name: Kecleon

abilities.name: Camouflage
abilities.text: If any basic Energy card attached to Kecleon is the same as the Attacking Pokémon's type, any damage done by attacks from the Pokémon to Kecleon is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Blind Scratch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does no damage to the Defending Pokémon. Instead, this attack does 20 damage to 1 of your Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It can freely change its body's color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn't change, however.

name: Kirlia

attacks.name: Psychic Research
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Supporter card and use the effect of that card as the effect of this attack. (The Supporter card remains in your discard pile.)

attacks.name: Telekinesis
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

flavorText: It is highly perceptive of its Trainer's feelings. It dances when it is feeling happy.

name: Lombre

attacks.name: Torment
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't play any Supporter cards from his or her hand during his or her next turn.

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters from Lombre.

flavorText: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.

name: Miltank

attacks.name: Healing Milk
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, remove 3 damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Continuous Tumble
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It is said that kids who drink MILTANK's milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.

name: Muk

abilities.name: Toxic Sludge
abilities.text: At the end of each player's turn, each of your opponent's Active Pokémon that has any Grass Energy attached to it is now Poisoned. If that Pokémon is already Poisoned, Toxic Sludge Poké-Body does nothing to that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Panic Liquid
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused and can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: A toxic fluids seeps from its body. The fluid instantly kills plants and trees on contact.

name: Nidorino

attacks.name: Spirited Drill
attacks.text: During your next turn, each of Nidorino's attacks does 20 more damage to the Defending Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Poison Horn
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes poison upon impact.

name: Pidgeotto

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.

name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Grip and Squeeze
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Power Guillotine
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack's base damage is 10 instead of 100.

flavorText: It grips prey with its pincers until the prey is torn in half. What it can't tear, it tosses far.

name: Quagsire

abilities.name: Aqua Healing
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Quagsire is your Active Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon has any Water Energy attached to it, you may remove 3 damage counters from Quagsire.

attacks.name: Muddy Water
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It has a sluggish nature. It lies at the river's bottom, waiting for prey to stray into its mouth.

name: Raticate

attacks.name: Gnaw Off
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 60 more damage.

attacks.name: Sneaky Attack
attacks.text: If Raticate has any Darkness Energy attached to it, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: It whittles its constantly growing fangs by gnawing on hard things. It can chew apart cinder walls.

name: Roselia

attacks.name: Sleep Powder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: ROSELIA raised on clean drinking water are known to grow vividly colored flowers.

name: Sableye

attacks.name: Rummage
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck. Choose as many Trainer cards as you like, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Put the other cards back on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Shadow Sneak
attacks.text: If you and your opponent have a different number of Prize cards left, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.

name: Shelgon

attacks.name: Focus Energy
attacks.text: During your next turn, Shelgon's Protect Charge attack's base damage is 80.

attacks.name: Protect Charge
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Shelgon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.

name: Skiploom

abilities.name: Cotton Balloon
abilities.text: If Skiploom has any Grass Energy attached to it, any damage done to Skiploom by attacks from your opponent's Evolved Pokémon is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: U-turn
attacks.text: Switch Skiploom with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.

name: Smeargle

attacks.name: Color Pick
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Trace
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose an attack on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. Trace copies that attack except for its Energy cost. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.) Smeargle performs that attack.

flavorText: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.

name: Smoochum

abilities.name: Baby Evolution
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put Jynx from your hand onto Smoochum (this counts as evolving Smoochum) and remove all damage counters from Smoochum.

attacks.name: Psykiss
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a Special Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon and have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.

flavorText: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.

name: Unown [K]

abilities.name: Kind
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 2 damage counters from 1 of the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: Unown [N]

abilities.name: Nod
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown N, Unown O, and Unown D on your Bench, you may ask your opponent to take a Prize card. If he or she does, you take a Prize card. If he or she doesn't, draw a card.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: Unown [O]

abilities.name: ONE
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown O, Unown N, and Unown E on your Bench and you have 1 card left in your hand, you may draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: Unown [X]

abilities.name: X-RAY
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown X on your Bench, you may look at the top card of your opponent's deck and put it back on top of his or her deck.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: Unown [Z]

abilities.name: ZERO
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown Z is on your Bench and you have no cards in your deck, you may discard all cards attached to Unown Z and put Unown Z on top of your deck.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Remove as many damage counters as you like from each Unown you have in play. Put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: Venomoth

abilities.name: Dangerous Scales
abilities.text: If Venomoth is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Venomoth is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Disturbance Dive
attacks.text: Prevent all effects of an attack, excluding damage, done to Venomoth during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It flutters its wings to scatter dustlike scales. The scales leach toxins if they contact skin.

name: Vibrava

attacks.name: Sand Wind
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It violently shudders its wings, generating ultrasonic waves to induce headaches in people.

name: Wartortle

attacks.name: Giant Wave
attacks.text: Wartortle can't use Giant Wave during your next turn.

flavorText: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.

name: Bagon

attacks.name: Rage
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Bagon.

flavorText: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

name: Bulbasaur

attacks.name: Shake Vine
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Bullet Seed
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.

name: Burmy Plant Cloak

abilities.name: Wear Cloak
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Burmy Plant Cloak is your Active Pokémon, you may search your discard pile for a basic Grass Energy card and attach it to Burmy Plant Cloak.

attacks.name: Plant Cloak Tackle
attacks.text: If Burmy Plant Cloak has any Grass Energy attached to it, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: Burmy Sandy Cloak

abilities.name: Wear Cloak
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Burmy Sandy Cloak is your Active Pokémon, you may search your discard for a basic Fighting Energy card and attach it to Burmy Sandy Cloak.

attacks.name: Sandy Cloak Tackle
attacks.text: If Burmy Sandy Cloak has any Fighting Energy attached to it, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: Burmy Trash Cloak

abilities.name: Wear Cloak
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Burmy Trash Cloak is your Active Pokémon, you may search your discard for a basic Metal Energy card and attach it to Burmy Trash Cloak.

attacks.name: Trash Cloak Tackle
attacks.text: If Burmy Trash Cloak has any Metal Energy attached to it, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: Carvanha

attacks.name: Bite Away
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

flavorText: They can swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.

name: Charmander

attacks.name: Lava Burn
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.

name: Clefairy
rules: Moon Stone: Clefairy can evolve during the turn you play it.

attacks.name: Double Slap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Corsola

attacks.name: Rally
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 different types of Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can't live in polluted waters.

name: Diglett

attacks.name: Down Draw
attacks.text: Draw a card from the bottom of your deck.

flavorText: A Pokémon that lives underground. Because of its dark habitat, it is repelled by bright sunlight.

name: Duskull
rules: Reaper Cloth: Duskull can evolve during the turn you play it.

attacks.name: Astonish
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking. Look at that card you chose, then have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.

name: Electabuzz

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Thunder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Electabuzz does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: Half of all blackouts occur when this Pokémon appears at power plants and eats electricity.

name: Grimer

attacks.name: Gunky
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

flavorText: It was born when sludge in a dirty stream was exposed to the moon's X-rays. It appears among filth.

name: Growlithe

attacks.name: Roar
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: A Pokémon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.

name: Hoppip

abilities.name: Cottonweed
abilities.text: If Hoppip has any Grass Energy attached to it, the Retreat Cost for Hoppip is 0.

attacks.name: Hover Heal
attacks.text: Remove all Special Conditions from Hoppip.

flavorText: It drifts on winds. It is said that when HOPPIP gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

name: Lickitung

attacks.name: Lick
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Stomp
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: Instead of hands, it uses its tongue, which is twice its height. Its sticky saliva grips anything.

name: Lotad

attacks.name: Water Sport
attacks.text: If Lotad has less Energy attached to it than the Defending Pokémon, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry to Pokémon that can't swim.

name: Magmar

attacks.name: Smog
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Born in the spout of a volcano, its body is covered by flames that shimmer like the sun.

name: Mareep

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Its fluffy coat swells to double when static electricity builds up. Touching it can be shocking.

name: Murkrow
rules: Dusk Stone: Murkrow can evolve during the turn you play it.

attacks.name: Feint Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

name: Natu

attacks.name: Bothering Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Future Sight
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of either player's deck and put them back on top of that player's deck in any order.

flavorText: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.

name: Nidoran ♂

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Poison Skin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.

name: Phanpy

attacks.name: Flail
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Phanpy.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: Phanpy does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

name: Pidgey

attacks.name: Growl
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

name: Psyduck

attacks.name: Delusion
attacks.text: If Psyduck is Confused, draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Migraine
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. If tails, Psyduck is now Confused.

flavorText: If its usual headache worsens, its starts exhibiting odd powers. It can't remember doing so, however.

name: Qwilfish

abilities.name: Balloon Sting
abilities.text: Once during your opponent's turn, if Qwilfish is your Active Pokémon and is damage by an attack (even if Qwilfish is Knocked Out), you may flip a coin. If heads, the Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokémon between turns.

attacks.name: Nerve Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

name: Ralts

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: It uses the thorns on its head to sense human emotions. It is said to appear in front of cheerful people.

name: Rattata

attacks.name: Tail Whip
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: Cautious in the extreme, its hardy vitality lets it live in any kind of environment.

name: Sentret

attacks.name: Grope
attacks.text: Look at the top 2 cards of your deck, choose 1 of them, and put it into your hand. Put the other card on the bottom of your deck.

flavorText: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.

name: Shellder

attacks.name: Shell Rest
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters from Shellder.

flavorText: It swims backwards by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.

name: Shellos East Sea

attacks.name: Shell Hunting
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 in any combination of Shellos West Sea and Shellos East Sea and put them on your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.

name: Shellos West Sea

attacks.name: Recover
attacks.text: Discard a Water Energy attached to Shellos West Sea and remove all damage counters from Shellos West Sea.

flavorText: Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.

name: Shroomish

attacks.name: Toxic Spore
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

name: Shuckle

abilities.name: Pot Shell
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Shuckle by your opponent's Pokémon that has any Special Energy cards attached to it.

attacks.name: Ferment Poison
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. As long as the Defending Pokémon remains Poisoned by this attack, it can't use any Poké-Body.

flavorText: It stores berries in its shell. The berries eventually ferment to become delicious juices.

name: Shuppet

attacks.name: Gossip
attacks.text: Put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.

name: Spinda

attacks.name: Dish Out
attacks.text: Draw a card from the top and the bottom of your deck.

attacks.name: Synchro Punch
attacks.text: If any basic Energy card attached to Spinda is the same type as any Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.

name: Squirtle

attacks.name: Bubble
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Aqua Tail
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Water Energy attached to Squirtle. This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

name: Stantler

attacks.name: Lead
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Supporter card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Frighten Horn
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon isn't an Evolved Pokémon, that Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.

name: Sunkern

attacks.name: Sun Soak
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from Sunkern, search your deck for an Evolution card that evolves from Sunkern, and put it onto Sunkern. (This counts as evolving Sunkern.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. A year after a cold summer, their population explodes.

name: Trapinch

attacks.name: Inviting Trap
attacks.text: Switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Sand Tomb
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It makes a conical pit in desert sand and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

name: Venonat

attacks.name: Stun Spore
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Signal Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At nights, its kind is drawn by light.

name: Voltorb

attacks.name: Big Explosion
attacks.text: Voltorb does 50 damage to itself.

flavorText: It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.

name: Wooper

attacks.name: Yawn
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Splatter
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

flavorText: It lives in cold water, half burying itself in mud at the bottom to sleep.

name: Bebe's Search
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.

Choose a card from your hand and put it on top of your deck. Search your deck for a Pokémon, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. (If this is the only card in your hand, you can't play this card.)

name: Night Maintenance
rules: Search your discard pile for up to 3 in any combination of Pokémon and basic Energy cards. Show them to your opponent and shuffle them into your deck.

name: PlusPower
rules: Attach PlusPower to 1 of your Pokémon. Discard this card at the end of your turn.
If the Pokémon PlusPower is attached to attacks, the attack does 10 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Professor Oak's Visit
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Draw 3 cards. Then, choose a card from your hand and put it on the bottom of your deck.

name: Professor Rowan
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Choose 1 card in your hand and shuffle the rest of your cards into your deck. Then, draw 4 cards. (If this is the only card in your hand, you can't play this card.)

name: Rival
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Reveal the top 5 cards of your deck. Your opponent chooses 3 of those cards. Put those cards into your hand and put other 2 cards on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Roseanne's Research
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Search your deck for up to 2 in any combination of Basic Pokémon and basic Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Team Galactic's Mars
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Draw 2 cards. Then, choose a card from your opponent's hand without looking and put it on the bottom of his or her deck.

name: Potion
rules: Remove 2 damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon (remove 1 damage counter if that Pokémon has only 1).

name: Switch
rules: Switch 1 of your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Darkness Energy
rules: If the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to attacks, the attack does 10 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance). Ignore this effect if the Pokémon that Darkness Energy is attached to isn't Darkness. Darkness Energy provides Darkness Energy. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: Metal Energy
rules: Damage done by attacks to the Pokémon that Metal Energy is attached to is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance). Ignore this effect if the Pokémon that Metal Energy is attached to isn't Metal. Metal Energy provides Metal Energy. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: Gardevoir LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Gardevoir. Gardevoir LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Teleportation
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), choose 1 of your Active Pokémon or 1 or your Benched Pokémon and switch Gardevoir with that Pokémon. This power can't be used if Gardevoir is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Bring Down
attacks.text: Choose 1 Pokémon (yours or your opponent's) with the fewest remaining HP (excluding Gardevoir) and that Pokémon is now Knocked Out.

name: Honchkrow LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Honchkrow. Honchkrow LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

attacks.name: Feint Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Darkness Wing
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon would be Knocked Out by damage from this attack, you may search your discard pile for any 1 card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand.

name: Blaziken

attacks.name: Fire Dance
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Fire Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Flame Kick
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy attached to Blaziken. This attack does 80 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.

name: Cresselia

attacks.name: Moon Twinkle
attacks.text: If there is any Stadium card in play, remove 2 damage counters from Cresselia.

attacks.name: Lunar Dance
attacks.text: You may discard 2 Energy attached to Cresselia. If you do, remove all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Darkrai

attacks.name: Reach Over
attacks.text: Search your deck for an Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Darkness Pursuit
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Cresselia, this attack's base damage is 100.

flavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: Darkrai

attacks.name: Darkness Roar
attacks.text: You may have your opponent switch the Defending Pokémon with 1 or his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Sleep Hole
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Asleep, this attack does 40 damage plus 40 more damage. If the Defending Pokémon is not Asleep, that Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: Pachirisu

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Smash Short
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage. Discard that Pokémon Tool card, look at your opponent's hand, and discard any Pokémon Tool cards of the same name you find there.

flavorText: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

name: Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Conversion
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a basic Energy card from your hand. Porygon-Z is the same type as that Energy Card until the end of your turn. This power can't be used if Porygon-Z is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Tri Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

name: Rotom

attacks.name: Astonish
attacks.text: Choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking. Look at that card you chose, then have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Telebeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

name: Sceptile

abilities.name: Wild Growth
abilities.text: Each basic Grass Energy card attached to your Grass Pokémon provides GrassGrass Energy instead. You can't use more than 1 Wild Growth Poké-Body each turn.

attacks.name: Leaf Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.

name: Swampert

abilities.name: Wash Out
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Water or Fighting Energy attached to 1 of your Benched Pokémon to your Active Pokémon. This power can't be used if Swampert is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hammer Arm
attacks.text: Discard the top card from your opponent's deck.

flavorText: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.

name: Tangrowth

attacks.name: Power Whip
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage for each basic Energy card attached to Tangrowth to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Stick and Absorb
attacks.text: Remove 3 damage counters from Tangrowth. The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

name: Togekiss

abilities.name: Serene Grace
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play Togekiss from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may look at the top 10 cards of your deck, choose as many basic Energy cards as you like, and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Put the other cards back on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Air Scroll
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage. If tails, remove 3 damage counters from Togekiss.

flavorText: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.

name: Altaria

attacks.name: Dragonbreath
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Cotton Cloud
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Altaria by attacks from your opponent's Evolved Pokémon is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: It looks like a fluffy cloud when it is in flight. It hums with its soprano voice.

name: Beedrill

attacks.name: Band Attack
attacks.text: Does 30 damage times the number of Beedrill you have in play.

attacks.name: Twineedle
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.

name: Butterfree

attacks.name: Parallel Drain
attacks.text: After your attack, remove from 1 of your Pokémon the number of damage counters equal to the damage you did to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dozing Scales
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

name: Claydol

abilities.name: Cosmic Power
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose up to 2 cards from your hand and put them on the bottom of your deck in any order. If you do, draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. This power can't be used if Claydol is affected by a Special Condition.

flavorText: An ancient clay figurine that came to life as a Pokémon from exposure to a mysterious ray of light.

name: Dialga

attacks.name: Time Bellow
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Flash Cannon
attacks.text: You may return all Energy cards attached to Dialga to your hand. If you do, remove the highest Stage Evolution card from the Defending Pokémon and shuffle that card into your opponent's deck.

flavorText: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

name: Exploud

attacks.name: Ambient Noise
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If the first coin is heads, this attack does 50 damage to the Defending Pokémon. If the first coin is tails, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) If the second coin is heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. If the second coin is tails, your opponent can't play any Trainer, Supporter, or Stadium cards from his or her hand during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.

name: Houndoom

attacks.name: Dark Fang
attacks.text: Choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

attacks.name: Black Fire
attacks.text: You may discard a Fire or Darkness Energy attached to Houndoom. If you discard a Fire Energy, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned. If you discard a Darkness Energy, this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.

name: Hypno

attacks.name: Dream Catcher
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Asleep, move all damage counters from Hypno to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hypnoblast
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even if someone just woke up.

name: Kingler

attacks.name: Scissor Blow
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon would be be Knocked Out by this attack, Kingler does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

name: Lapras

attacks.name: Carry In
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Pokémon Tool Card, a Supporter card, and a basic Energy card, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokémon on its back. It understands human speech.

name: Latias

attacks.name: Miraculous Light
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters and all Special Conditions from Latias.

attacks.name: Mist Ball
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy and a Water Energy attached to Latias.

flavorText: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.

name: Latios

attacks.name: Energy Draw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to Latios. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Luster Purge
attacks.text: Discard 3 Energy attached to Latios.

flavorText: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

name: Mawile

attacks.name: Pick Out
attacks.text: Choose 1 face-down Prize card (yours or your opponent's) and put it face up. If that card is a Supporter card, use the effect of that card as the effect of this attack. (That card remains face up for the rest of the game.)

attacks.name: Jaw Bite
attacks.text: During your next turn, if an attack does damage to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.

name: Milotic

abilities.name: Marvel Scale
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Milotic by your opponent's Pokémon LV.X.

attacks.name: Twister
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both are tails, this attack does nothing. For each heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: When people bicker, it is said to arise from the depths of lakes to becalm violent hearts.

name: Palkia

attacks.name: Spacial Rend
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. If there is any Stadium card in play, discard it.

attacks.name: Transback
attacks.text: You may flip a coin. If heads, discard all Energy attached to Palkia and put the Defending Pokémon and all cards attached to it on top of your opponent's deck. Your opponent shuffles his or her deck afterward.

flavorText: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

name: Primeape

abilities.name: Anger Point
abilities.text: If Primeape has any damage counters on it, Primeape's attacks do 40 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Whump
attacks.text: Primeape is now Confused. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.

name: Slowking

abilities.name: Trump Card
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn, search your deck for any 1 card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Slowking is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Psych Up
attacks.text: During your next turn, Slowking's Psych Up attack's base damage is 60.

flavorText: Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.

name: Unown [H]

abilities.name: HEAL
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown H, Unown E, Unown A, and Unown L on your Bench, you may remove all Special Conditions from 1 of your Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Discard a card from your hand. (If you can't discard a card from your hand, this attack does nothing.)

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: Wailord

abilities.name: Sleeping Pulse
abilities.text: As long as Wailord remains Asleep between turns, remove 1 damage counter from Wailord.

attacks.name: Sink Deep
attacks.text: If Wailord has any damage counters on it, Wailord is now Asleep.

flavorText: The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.

name: Weezing

abilities.name: Toxic Virus
abilities.text: At any time between turns, each player puts 1 more damage counter on his or her Poisoned Pokémon.

attacks.name: Offensive Gas
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

flavorText: It grows by feeding on gases released by garbage. Though very rare, triplets have been found.

name: Wigglytuff

abilities.name: Good Night Melody
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Each Active Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) is now Asleep. This power can't be used if Wigglytuff is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Ballon Attack
attacks.text: If Igglybuff is anywhere under Wigglytuff, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: Its fine fur feels sublime to the touch. It can expand its body by inhaling air.

name: Arbok

attacks.name: Deadly Poison
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 10 damage plus 40 more damage. If the Defending Pokémon is not Poisoned, that Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Wrap
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.

name: Cacturne

attacks.name: Pin Missile
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Needle Arm
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day's desert heat.

name: Combusken

attacks.name: Bulk Up
attacks.text: During your next turn, each of Combusken's attacks does 30 more damage to the Defending Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Double Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.

name: Delibird

attacks.name: Present
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for any 1 card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It carries food rolled up in its tail. It has the habit of sharing food with people lost in mountains.

name: Floatzel

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Floatzel during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Aqua Jet
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It floats using its well-developed floatation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

name: Gorebyss

attacks.name: Sweet Temptation
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with 1 of the Defending Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to the new Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psychic Snap
attacks.text: If Gorebyss has any Psychic Energy attached to it, this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.

name: Granbull

attacks.name: Daunt
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Rage
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Granbull.

flavorText: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.

name: Grovyle

attacks.name: Greenness
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Grass Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Poison Breath
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

name: Hariyama

attacks.name: Palm Strike
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 40 more damage.

attacks.name: Spirited Throw
attacks.text: If Hariyama has fewer remaining HP than the Defending Pokémon, this attack's base damage is 80.

flavorText: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

name: Huntail

attacks.name: Scary Face
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack or retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Threaten and Drop
attacks.text: If Huntail has any Darkness Energy attached to it, this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage and discard a Special Energy card, if any, attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

name: Linoone

attacks.name: Switcheroo
attacks.text: Move a Pokémon Tool card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon to another of your opponent's Pokémon (excluding Pokémon that already has a Pokémon Tool attached to it). (If an effect of this attack is prevented, this attack does nothing.)

attacks.name: Overrun
attacks.text: Does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.

name: Loudred

attacks.name: Bass Control
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Stomp
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.

name: Magcargo

abilities.name: Magma Armor
abilities.text: Magcargo can't be Asleep or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Lava Plume
attacks.text: You may discard the top card of your deck. If you do, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees F. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.

name: Marshtomp

attacks.name: Muddy Bomb
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon and 10 damage to each of your opponent's other Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.

name: Metapod

abilities.name: Emerge
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Metapod is your Active Pokémon, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a card that evolves from Metapod and put it onto Metapod. (This counts as evolving Metapod.) Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Metapod is affected by a Special Condition.

flavorText: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

name: Pelipper

attacks.name: Guzzle
attacks.text: Choose up to 2 basic Water Energy cards from your hand and attach them to Pelipper. Remove 2 damage counters for each Energy card attached in this way.

attacks.name: Jet Return
attacks.text: Does 30 times the number of Energy cards attached to Pelipper. Then, put all Energy cards attached to Pelipper on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It dips its large bill in the sea, then scoops up numerous prey along with water.

name: Porygon2

abilities.name: Download
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Supporter card from your hand and use the effect of that card as the effect of this power. This power can't be used if Porygon2 is affected by a Special Condition.

flavorText: With planetary development software installed, it became capable of working in space.

name: Purugly

attacks.name: Swagger
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon's nest and claims it as its own.

name: Relicanth

attacks.name: Primal Calling
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Trainer Cards that have Fossil in their names, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Sleep Swirl
attacks.text: Both Relicanth and the Defending Pokémon are now Asleep.

flavorText: A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

name: Seviper

attacks.name: Tail Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't play any Trainer cards from his or her hand during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Poison Tail
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage and the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: For many generations, it has feuded with ZANGOOSE. It whets its bladed tail on rocks for battle.

name: Skarmory

attacks.name: Air Crash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Steel Wing
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Skarmory by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Despite being clad entirely in iron-hard armor, it flies at speeds over 180 mph.

name: Slowbro

attacks.name: Amnesia
