attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the SHELLDER on its tail bites down.

name: Togetic

attacks.name: Sweet Kiss
attacks.text: Your opponent may draw a card.

flavorText: It is said to appear in front of kindly people to scatter a glowing down called "joy dust."

name: Unown [F]

abilities.name: FAKE
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown F is on your Bench, you may use this power. Put a coin next to your Active Pokémon without showing your opponent and cover it with your hand. Your opponent guesses if the coin is heads or tails. If he or she is wrong, draw a card.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: You may flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, this attack's base damage is 30.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: Unown [G]

abilities.name: GUARD
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown G is on your Bench, you may discard all cards attached to Unown G and attach Unown G to 1 of your Pokémon as a Pokémon Tool card. As long as Unown G is attached to a Pokémon, prevent all effects of attacks, excluding damage, done to that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: If Unown G has any damage counters on it, this attack's base damage is 10.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: Wailmer

attacks.name: Tsunami
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose.

name: Zangoose

attacks.name: Cutting Claw
attacks.text: If your opponent has Seviper in play, this attack does 40 damage plus 50 more damage.

flavorText: It has feuded with SEVIPER for many generations. Its sharp claws are its biggest weapons.

name: Baltoy

attacks.name: Psychic Balance
attacks.text: If you have less cards in your hand than your opponent, draw cards until you have the same number of cards as your opponent. (If you have more or the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does nothing.)

attacks.name: Spin Turn
attacks.text: Switch Baltoy with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It moves by spinning on its foot. It is a rare Pokémon that was discovered in ancient ruins.

name: Buizel
flavorText: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.

name: Cacnea

attacks.name: Sand Attack
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: By storing water in its body, this desert dweller can survive 30 days without water.

name: Caterpie

abilities.name: Pupate
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Caterpie is your Active Pokémon, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a card that evolves from Caterpie and put it onto Caterpie. (This counts as evolving Caterpie.) Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Caterpie is affected by a Special Condition.

flavorText: It releases a stench from its red antenna to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.

name: Clamperl

attacks.name: Clamp
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.

name: Drowzee

attacks.name: Hypnosis
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.

name: Ekans

attacks.name: Shed Skin
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters from Ekans.

attacks.name: Poison Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.

name: Feebas

attacks.name: Fast Evolution
attacks.text: Search your deck for an Evolution card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: It is famous for its shabby appearance. While populous, they tend to cluster in set locations.

name: Glameow

attacks.name: Captivate
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with 1 of the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

name: Houndour

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard a Fire Energy attached to Houndour.

flavorText: It conveys its feelings using different cries. It works in a pack to cleverly take down prey.

name: Igglybuff

abilities.name: Baby Evolution
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put Jigglypuff from your hand onto Igglybuff (this counts as evolving Igglybuff) and remove all damage counters from Igglybuff.

attacks.name: Inquire
attacks.text: Draw a card. If you didn't play any Supporter card from your hand during this turn, draw 2 more cards.

flavorText: It has a soft and bouncy body. Once it starts bouncing, it becomes impossible to stop.

name: Illumise

abilities.name: Scent Conduct
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Grass Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Illumise is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Firefly Scent
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon has any Poké-Bodies, that Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: With its sweet aroma, it guides VOLBEAT to draw signs with light in the night sky.

name: Jigglypuff

attacks.name: Hypnotic Gaze
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Expand
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Jigglypuff by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: When it wavers its big, round eyes, it begins singing a lullaby that makes everyone drowsy.

name: Kakuna

attacks.name: Stiffen
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Kakuna by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Spit Poison
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

name: Koffing

attacks.name: Smogscreen
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

flavorText: Lighter-than-air gases in its body keep it aloft. The gases not only smell, they are also explosive.

name: Krabby
flavorText: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.

name: Lunatone

abilities.name: Gravity Change
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a card from your hand. Then, if you have Solrock in play, draw a card. This power can't be used if Lunatone is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Knock Over
attacks.text: You may discard any Stadium card in play.

flavorText: Because it turns active on nights of the full moon, it is said to have some link to the lunar phases.

name: Luvdisc

attacks.name: Rendezvous
attacks.text: Reveal the top card of your deck and put it into your hand. If that card is a Pokémon, draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Synchro Dance
attacks.text: If Luvdisc and the Defending Pokémon have the same amount of Energy attached to them, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.

name: Makuhita

attacks.name: Arm Thrust
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It toughens its body by slamming into thick trees. Many snapped trees can be found near its nest.

name: Mankey

attacks.name: Rage
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Mankey.

flavorText: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

name: Mudkip

attacks.name: Endeavor
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

name: Porygon

attacks.name: Calculate
attacks.text: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck and put them back on top of your deck in any order.

flavorText: The world's first artificially created Pokémon. It can travel through electronic space.

name: Slowpoke

attacks.name: Rest
attacks.text: Remove all Special Conditions and 3 damage counters from Slowpoke. Slowpoke is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Tumble Over
attacks.text: Slowpoke can't attack during your next turn.

flavorText: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.

name: Slugma

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

name: Snubbull

attacks.name: Roar
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

name: Solrock

abilities.name: Sunlight
abilities.text: If you have Lunatone in play, damage done to your opponent's Pokémon by your Psychic or Fighting Pokémon isn't affected by resistance.

attacks.name: Sol Charge
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: A new Pokémon species, rumored to be from the sun. It gives off light while spinning.

name: Swablu

attacks.name: Super Speed
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Swablu during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Shoot Through
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Its wings are like cotton tufts. If it perches on someone's head, it looks like a cotton hat.

name: Tangela

attacks.name: Vine Invite
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with 1 of the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Grass Knot
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Colorless Energy in the Defending Pokémon's Retreat Cost (after applying effects to the the Retreat Cost).

flavorText: It is shrouded by blue vines. No one has seen the face hidden behind this growth of vines.

name: Togepi

attacks.name: Yawn
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Pokémon, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: Its shell is said to be stuffed with happiness that it shares with kindhearted people.

name: Torchic

attacks.name: Singe
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.

name: Treecko

attacks.name: Energy Ball
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to Treecko but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from Treecko.

flavorText: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

name: Unown [L]

abilities.name: LINK
abilities.text: Unown L can use any attack from any Unown in play (both yours and your opponent's). (You still have to pay for that attack's Energy cost.)

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Search either player's discard pile for up to any 2 cards, show them to your opponent, and put them on top of that player's deck in any order you like.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or UNOWN came first.

name: Volbeat

abilities.name: Light Conduct
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Illumise in play, you may search your discard pile for a Supporter card, show it to your opponent, and put it on top of your deck. This power can't be used if Volbeat is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Firefly Light
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves ILLUMISE's sweet aroma.

name: Weedle

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: String Shot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.

name: Whismur

attacks.name: Uproar
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs.  If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.

name: Wingull
flavorText: It makes its nest on steep sea cliffs. Riding updrafts, it soars to great heights.

name: Zigzagoon

attacks.name: Pull Out
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for any 1 card, show it to your opponent, and put it on top of your deck.

attacks.name: Double Stab
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It walks in zigzag fashion. It is good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.

name: Amulet Coin
rules: Attach Amulet Coin to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't already have a Pokémon Tool attached to it. If that Pokémon is Knocked Out, discard this card.
If the Pokémon Amulet Coin is attached to is your Active Pokémon at the end of your turn, draw a card.

name: Felicity's Drawing
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Discard up to 2 cards from your hand. If you discard 1 card, draw 3 cards. If you discard 2 cards, draw 4 cards.

name: Leftovers
rules: Attach Leftovers to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't already have a Pokémon Tool attached to it. If that Pokémon is Knocked Out, discard this card.
If the Pokémon Leftovers is attached to is your Active Pokémon at the end of your turn, remove 1 damage counter from the Pokémon.

name: Moonlight Stadium
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play. If another card with the same name is in play, you can't play this card.
The Retreat Cost for each Psychic and Darkness Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) is 0.

name: Premier Ball
rules: Search your deck or your discard pile for a Pokémon LV.X, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. If you search your deck, shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Rare Candy
rules: Choose 1 of your Basic Pokémon in play. If you have a Stage 1 or Stage 2 card that evolves from that Pokémon in your hand, put that card on the Basic Pokémon. (This counts as evolving that Pokémon.)

name: Cresselia LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Cresselia. Cresselia LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Full Moon Dance
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from either player's Pokémon to another Pokémon (yours or your opponent's). This power can't be used if Cresselia is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Moon Skip
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out by this attack, take 1 more Prize card.

name: Darkrai LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Darkrai. Darkrai LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Dark Shadow
abilities.text: Each basic Darkness Energy card attached to your Darkness Pokémon now has the effect "If the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to attacks, the attack does 10 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance)." You can't use more than 1 Dark Shadow Poké-Body each turn.

attacks.name: Endless Darkness
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. Flip 2 coins instead of 1 between turns. If either of them is tails, the Defending Pokémon is still Asleep. If both of them are tails, the Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out.

name: Dialga LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Dialga. Dialga LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Time Skip
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may have your opponent flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, your turn ends. If both of them are tails, after your opponent draws a card at the beginning of his or her next turn, his or her turn ends. This power can't be used if Dialga is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Metal Flash
attacks.text: During your next turn, Dialga can't use Metal Flash.

name: Palkia LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Palkia. Palkia LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Restructure
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may have your opponent switch 1 of your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. Then, you switch 1 of the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This power can't be used if Palkia is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hydro Reflect
attacks.text: You may move all Energy cards attached to Palkia to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like. (Ignore this effect if you don't have any Benched Pokémon.)

name: Articuno

abilities.name: Freezing Screech
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Articuno from your hand onto your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon. That Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Blizzard
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

name: Cresselia

attacks.name: Future Sight
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of either player's deck and put them back on top of that player's deck in any order.

attacks.name: Healing Light
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokémon.

flavorText: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Darkrai

abilities.name: Darkness Shade
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Darkrai from your hand onto your Bench, you may choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon. That Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Dark Slumber
attacks.text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Dark Resolve
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Asleep, remove 4 damage counters from Darkrai.

flavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: Dialga
rules: Adamant Orb: If an Active Pokémon has Weakness to Metal type, Dialga's attacks do 20 more damage to that Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Time Shift
attacks.text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Diamond Blast
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Glaceon

attacks.name: Snow Cloak
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Glaceon during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Speed Slide
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

name: Kabutops

abilities.name: Primal Shell
abilities.text: As long as Kabutops is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Trainer cards from his or her hand.

attacks.name: Chop Up
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

name: Leafeon

attacks.name: Bind Down
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Leaf Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Leafeon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

name: Manaphy

abilities.name: Aqua Skin
abilities.text: When you attach a Water Energy card from your hand to Manaphy, remove 2 damage counters from Manaphy.

attacks.name: Chase Up
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for any 1 card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Fountain
attacks.text: You may attach up to 2 basic Water Energy cards from your hand to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

flavorText: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Energy Absorption
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for up to 2 Energy cards and attach them to Mewtwo.

attacks.name: Recover
attacks.text: Discard a Psychic Energy attached to Mewtwo and remove 6 damage counters from Mewtwo.

flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

name: Moltres

abilities.name: Flame Charge
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Moltres from your hand onto your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for up to 3 Fire Energy cards and attach them to Moltres.

attacks.name: Scorching Wing
attacks.text: Discard all Fire Energy attached to Moltres.

flavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

name: Palkia
rules: Lustrous Orb: If an Active Pokémon has Weakness to Water type, Palkia's attacks do 20 more damage to that Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Zone Shift
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Pearl Blast
attacks.text: You may return an Energy card attached to Palkia to your hand. If you do, choose an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon and return it to your opponent's hand.

name: Phione

attacks.name: Evolution Wish
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of your Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon. (This counts as evolving that Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Water Pulse
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.

name: Rotom

attacks.name: Dual Trans
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for up to 2 basic Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Reflect Energy
attacks.text: Move an Energy card attached to Rotom to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

name: Zapdos

abilities.name: Sheet Lightning
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Zapdos from your hand onto your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Raging Thunder
attacks.text: Does 40 damage to 1 of your Pokémon, and don't apply Weakness and Resistance to this damage.

flavorText: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

name: Aerodactyl

abilities.name: Primal Claw
abilities.text: After your opponent's Pokémon uses a Poké-Power, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Supersonic
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: A Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

name: Bronzong

abilities.name: Cursed Alloy
abilities.text: As long as Bronzong is your Active Pokémon, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon that has any Poké-Powers between turns.

attacks.name: Pain Amplifier
attacks.text: Put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon that already has damage counters on it.

attacks.name: Coating
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Bronzong by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.

name: Empoleon

attacks.name: Dual Splash
attacks.text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to each of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Surf Together
attacks.text: Does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon. Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.

name: Espeon

abilities.name: Sunlight Veil
abilities.text: Each of your Pokémon that evolves from Eevee gets +20 HP. You can't use more than 1 Sunlight Veil Poké-Body each turn.

attacks.name: Morning Sun
attacks.text: You may move an Energy card attached to Espeon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Its fur has the look and feel of velvet. The orb on its forehead glows when it uses psycho-power.

name: Flareon

attacks.name: Fire Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Kindle
attacks.text: Discard an Energy card attached to Flareon and then discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It has a flame sac in its body. Its body temperature tops 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit before battle.

name: Glaceon

attacks.name: Ice Shot
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Icy Wind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

name: Hippowdon

attacks.name: Vacuum Sand
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Fighting Energy card and attach it to Hippowdon.

attacks.name: Sand Impact
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Fighting Energy attached to Hippowdon. This attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: Its huge mouth is almost seven feet across. It has enough power to completely crush a car.

name: Infernape

attacks.name: Mach Punch
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Mega Bravo
attacks.text: Discard all Fire Energy attached to Infernape. This attack does 40 damage times the amount of Fire Energy you discarded.

flavorText: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

name: Jolteon

attacks.name: Thunder Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Lightning Strike
attacks.text: You may discard 2 Energy attached to Jolteon. If you do, this attack's base damage is 90 instead of 50.

flavorText: It controls 10,000-volt power and can raise all the furs on its body as if it were sharp needles.

name: Leafeon

attacks.name: Sprial Drain
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from Leafeon.

attacks.name: Leaf Blade
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

name: Minun

attacks.name: (+) Spark
attacks.text: If Plusle is on your Bench, this attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

name: Omastar

abilities.name: Primal Swirl
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play Omastar from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may remove the highest Stage Evolution card from each of your opponent's Benched Evolved Pokémon and put those cards back into his or her hand. You can't use more than 1 Primal Swirl Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Send Back
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It is thought that this Pokémon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.

name: Phione

attacks.name: Charm
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.

name: Plusle

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: – Boost
attacks.text: If Minun is on your Bench, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

name: Scizor

attacks.name: Special Blow
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon has any Special Energy cards attached to it, this attack does 30 damage plus 50 more damage.

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 damage plus 40 more damage.

flavorText: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.

name: Torterra

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Frenzy Plant
attacks.text: Torterra can't use Frenzy Plant during your next turn.

flavorText: Groups of this Pokémon migrating in search of water have been mistaken for "moving forests."

name: Toxicroak

attacks.name: Paralyze Poison
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

flavorText: The toxin made in its poison sacs is pumped to the knuckle claws through tubes down its arms.

name: Umbreon

abilities.name: Moonlight Veil
abilities.text: Each of your Pokémon that evolves from Eevee has no Weakness, and that Pokémon's Retreat Cost is 0.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: The light of the moon changed Eevee's genetic structure. It lurks in darkness for prey.

name: Unown [P]

abilities.name: PUT
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown P is on your Bench, you may put 1 damage counter on 1 of your Pokémon (excluding any Unown).

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Each player discards the top card of his or her deck. This attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage for each Unown discarded in this way.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Vaporeon

attacks.name: Cleanse Away
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters from each of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hyper Whirlpool
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: It has evolved to be suitable for aquatic life. It can invisibly melt away into water.

name: Ambipom

attacks.name: Astonish
attacks.text: Choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking. Look at that card you chose, then have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Hang High
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

name: Fearow

attacks.name: Fury Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

name: Grotle

attacks.name: Planting
attacks.text: Attach a Grass Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: The shell is hardened soil. Some Pokémon come to peck the berries growing on the trees on its back.

name: Kangaskhan

attacks.name: Comet Punch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.

name: Lickitung

attacks.name: Lap Up
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: Instead of hands, it uses its tongue, which is twice its height. Its sticky saliva grips anything.

name: Manectric

attacks.name: Thunder Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Volt Crush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to Manectric and this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

name: Monferno

attacks.name: Fire Fang
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Mid-air Strike
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

name: Mothim

abilities.name: Disturbance Scales
abilities.text: Any damage done by attacks from your Pokémon to the Defending Pokémon isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Get Help
attacks.text: Does 30 damage times the number of different types of Wormadam on your Bench.

attacks.name: Quick Touch
attacks.text: You may switch Mothim with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, move as many Energy cards attached to Mothim as you like to the new Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.

name: Pachirisu

attacks.name: Trans Tail
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Lightning Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand.

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It makes electricity with pouches in its cheeks and shoots charges from its tail. It lives atop trees.

name: Prinplup

attacks.name: Ice Blade
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Wash Over
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Its wings deliver wicked blows that snap even the thickest of trees. It searches for prey in icy seas.

name: Raichu

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Raichu during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Thunderbolt
attacks.text: Discard all Energy cards attached to Raichu.

flavorText: It can loose 100,000-volt bursts of electricity, instantly downing foes several times its size.

name: Scyther

attacks.name: Fury Cutter
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. If 1 of them is heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage. If 2 of them are heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage. If all of them are heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 40 more damage.

flavorText: It is nearly impossible to parry its attacking scythes. Its movements are like a ninja's.

name: Staravia

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

name: Sudowoodo

attacks.name: Flail
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Sudowoodo.

attacks.name: Wood Hammer
attacks.text: Sudowoodo does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: It stands along paths pretending to be a tree. If it starts raining, it seems to disappear.

name: Unown [Q]

abilities.name: QUICK
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown Q is on your Bench, you may discard all cards attached to Unown Q and attach Unown Q to 1 of your Pokémon as a Pokémon Tool card. As long as Unown Q is attached to a Pokémon, you pay Colorless less to retreat that Pokémon.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Aipom

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Hand Trick
attacks.text: Return Aipom and all cards attached to it to your hand. (If you don't have any Benched Pokémon, this attack does nothing.)

flavorText: It lives atop giant trees. It wraps its tail around a branch so it won't fall off while asleep.

name: Aipom

attacks.name: Last Resort
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It uses its tail to pluck fruits that are out of reach. Its tail is more adept than its real hands.

name: Bronzor

attacks.name: Hypnosis
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: X-ray photos were taken to check its body structure. Nothing appeared, however.

name: Buneary

attacks.name: Drawup Power
attacks.text: Search your deck for an Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Extend Ears
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from each of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.

name: Burmy Sandy Cloak

attacks.name: Iron Defense
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Burmy Sandy Cloak during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

name: Chatot

attacks.name: Mimic
attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a number of cards equal to the number of cards in your opponent's hand.

attacks.name: Chatter
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: Chimchar

attacks.name: Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can't extinguish the fire.

name: Chimchar
rules: Cheri Berry: If Chimchar is Paralyzed, remove the Special Condition Paralyzed from Chimchar at the end of each player's turn.

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Chingling

abilities.name: Baby Evolution
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put Chimecho from your hand onto Chingling (this counts as evolving Chingling) and remove all damage counters from Chingling.

attacks.name: Uproar
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.

name: Combee

attacks.name: Honey Scent
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Flitter
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

flavorText: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

name: Croagunk

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it makes an eerie blubbering sound for intimidation.

name: Drifloon

attacks.name: Delivery
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, put any 1 card from your discard pile into your hand.

attacks.name: Reaction
attacks.text: Switch Drifloon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It tugs on the hands of children to steal them away. However, it gets pulled around instead.

name: Eevee

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for as many Eevee as you like and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: A rare Pokémon that adapts to harsh environments by taking on different evolutionary forms.

name: Eevee

attacks.name: Sand Attack
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

flavorText: A rare Pokémon that adapts to harsh environments by taking on different evolutionary forms.

name: Electrike

attacks.name: Random Spark
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.

name: Glameow

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Rip Claw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: With its sharp glare, it puts foes in a mild hypnotic state. It is a very fickle Pokémon.

name: Hippopotas

attacks.name: Grainy Sand
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

attacks.name: Double-edge
attacks.text: Hippopotas does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

name: Kabuto

abilities.name: Ancient Guidance
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for Helix Fossil, Dome Fossil, or Old Amber and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Kabuto is affected by a Special Condition.

flavorText: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a stiff shell.

name: Munchlax

abilities.name: Baby Evolution
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put Snorlax from your hand onto Munchlax (this counts as evolving Munchlax) and remove all damage counters from Munchlax.

attacks.name: Lick
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It hides food under its long body hair. However, it forgets it has hidden the food.

name: Omanyte

abilities.name: Call Up
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for Helix Fossil, Dome Fossil, or Old Amber and put it onto your Bench. This power can't be used if Omanyte is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Wash Over
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: A Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.

name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

attacks.name: Volt Tackle
attacks.text: Pikachu does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: If it looses crackling power from the electric pouches on its cheeks, it is being wary.

name: Piplup

attacks.name: Water Splash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: It lives along shores in northern countries. A skilled swimmer, it dives for over 10 minutes to hunt.

name: Piplup
rules: Pecha Berry: If Piplup is Poisoned, remove the Special Condition Poisoned from Piplup at the end of each player's turn.

attacks.name: Splatter
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Shellos East Sea

attacks.name: Muddy Water
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It lives along bodies of water. Its body shape changed to suit its habitat.

name: Spearow

attacks.name: Claw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.

name: Starly

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Usually with a large flock, it is barely noticeable when alone. Its cries are very strident.

name: Stunky

attacks.name: Poison Gas
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It sprays a nose-curling, stinky fluid from its rear to repel attackers.

name: Turtwig
flavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

name: Turtwig
rules: Persim Berry: If Turtwig is Confused, remove the Special Condition Confused from Turtwig at the end of each player's turn.

name: Dawn Stadium
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play. If another card with the same name is in play, you can't play this card.
Whenever any player attaches an Energy card from his or her hand to Grass Pokémon or Water Pokémon, remove 1 damage counter and all Special Conditions from that Pokémon.

name: Dusk Ball
rules: Look at the 7 cards from the bottom of your deck. Choose 1 Pokémon you find there, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Put the remaining cards back on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Energy Restore
rules: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, put a Basic Energy card from your discard pile into your hand. If you don't have that many basic Energy cards in your discard pile, put all of them into your hand.

name: Fossil Excavator
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.

Search your deck or discard pile for a Trainer card that has Fossil in its name or a Stage 1 or Stage 2 Evolution card that evolves from a Fossil. Show it to your opponent and put it into your hand. If you searched your deck, shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Mom's Kindness
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Draw 2 cards.

name: Old Amber
rules: Play Old Amber as if it were a Colorless Basic Pokémon. (Old Amber counts as a Trainer card as well, but if Old Amber is Knocked Out, this counts as a Knocked Out Pokémon.) Old Amber can't be affected by any Special Conditions and can't retreat. At any time during your turn before your attack, you may discard Old Amber from play. (This doesn't count as a Knocked Out Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Hard Amber
abilities.text: As long as Old Amber is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to Old Amber by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Poké Ball
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Pokémon, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Quick Ball
rules: Reveal cards from your deck until you reveal a Pokémon. Show that Pokémon to your opponent and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other revealed cards back into your deck. (If you don't reveal a Pokémon, shuffle all the revealed cards back into your deck.)

name: Super Scoop Up
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, return 1 of your Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your hand.

name: Warp Point
rules: Your opponent switches 1 of his or her Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon, if any. You switch 1 of your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon, if any.

name: Dome Fossil
rules: Play Dome Fossil as if it were a Colorless Basic Pokémon. (Dome Fossil counts as a Trainer card as well, but if Dome Fossil is Knocked Out, this counts as a Knocked Out Pokémon.) Dome Fossil can't be affected by any Special Conditions and can't retreat. At any time during your turn before your attack, you may discard Dome Fossil from play. (This doesn't count as a Knocked Out Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Rock Reaction
abilities.text: When you attach a Fighting Energy card from your hand to Dome Fossil (excluding effects of attacks or Poké-Powers), search your deck for a card that evolves from Dome Fossil and put it onto Dome Fossil (this counts as evolving Dome Fossil). Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Energy Search
rules: Search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Helix Fossil
rules: Play Helix Fossil as if it were a Colorless Basic Pokémon. (Helix Fossil counts as a Trainer card as well, but if Helix Fossil is Knocked Out, this counts as a Knocked Out Pokémon.) Helix Fossil can't be affected by any Special Conditions and can't retreat. At any time during your turn before your attack, you may discard Helix Fossil from play. (This doesn't count as a Knocked Out Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Aqua Reaction
abilities.text: When you attach a Water Energy card from your hand to Helix Fossil (excluding effects of attacks or Poké-Powers), search your deck for a card that evolves from Helix Fossil and put it onto Helix Fossil (this counts as evolving Helix Fossil). Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Call Energy
rules: Call Energy provides Colorless Energy. Once during your turn, if the Pokémon Call Energy is attached to is your Active Pokémon, you may search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. If you do, shuffle your deck and your turn ends.

name: Darkness Energy
rules: If the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to attacks, the attack does 10 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance). Ignore this effect if the Pokémon that Darkness Energy is attached to isn't Darkness. Darkness Energy provides Darkness Energy. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: Health Energy
rules: Health Energy provides Colorless Energy. When you attach this card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon, remove 1 damage counter from that Pokémon.

name: Metal Energy
rules: Damage done by attacks to the Pokémon that Metal Energy is attached to is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance). Ignore this effect if the Pokémon that Metal Energy is attached to isn't Metal. Metal Energy provides Metal Energy. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: Recover Energy
rules: Recover Energy provides Colorless Energy. When you attach this card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon, remove all Special Conditions from that Pokémon.

name: Garchomp LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Garchomp. Garchomp LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Dragon Pulse
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Garchomp LV.X from your hand onto your Active Garchomp, you may flip 3 coins. For each heads, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Restore
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Pokémon (excluding Pokémon LV.X) and put it onto your Bench as a Basic Pokémon. Then, you may search your discard pile for up to 3 basic Energy cards and attach them to that Pokémon.

name: Glaceon LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Glaceon. Glaceon LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Chilly Breath
abilities.text: As long as Glaceon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Pokémon can't use any Poké-Powers.

attacks.name: Avalanche
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Leafeon LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Leafeon. Leafeon LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Energy Forcing
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Leafeon is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Verdant Dance
attacks.text: Does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

name: Porygon-Z LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Porygon-Z. Porygon-Z LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Mode Crash
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Porygon-Z LV.X from your hand onto your Active Porygon-Z, you may discard all of your opponent's Special Energy cards in play.

abilities.name: Decode
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for up to any 2 cards and shuffle your deck afterward. Then, put those cards on top of your deck in any order. This power can't be used if Porygon-Z is affected by a Special Condition.

name: Deoxys Normal Forme

abilities.name: Form Change
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for any Deoxys and switch it with Deoxys Normal Forme. (Any cards attached to Deoxys Normal Forme, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) If you do, put Deoxys Normal Forme on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward. You can't use more than 1 Form Change Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Energy Crush
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: Dragonite

attacks.name: Hyper Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Draco Meteor
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each of your opponent's Pokémon. If that coin flip is heads, this attack does 50 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

name: Froslass

attacks.name: Destiny Bond
attacks.text: Discard a Psychic Energy attached to Froslass. During your opponent's next turn, if Froslass would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, the Attacking Pokémon is Knocked Out.

attacks.name: Icy Breath
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. Put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees F. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

name: Giratina

attacks.name: Shadow Force
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Giratina during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Brutal Edge
attacks.text: Does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

name: Gliscor

attacks.name: Burning Poison
attacks.text: Choose either Burned or Poisoned. The Defending Pokémon is now affected by that Special Condition. You may return Gliscor and all cards attached to it to your hand.

attacks.name: Pester
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 40 damage plus 40 more damage.

flavorText: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

name: Heatran

abilities.name: Flash Fire
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Fire Energy attached to 1 of your Pokémon to Heatran. This power can't be used if Heatran is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Magma Storm
attacks.text: You may discard as many basic Energy cards as you like attached to Heatran. If you do, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage for each Energy card you discarded.

flavorText: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Kingdra

attacks.name: Aqua Stream
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for as many Water Energy cards as you like, show them to your opponent, and this attack does 10 damage for each Water Energy card you chose. Put those cards on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Dragon Pump
attacks.text: You may discard 2 cards from your hand. If you do, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage and does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.

name: Luxray

abilities.name: Rivalry
abilities.text: If your opponent has any Pokémon LV.X in play, each of Luxray's attacks does 50 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Plasma
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to Luxray.

attacks.name: Shock Bolt
attacks.text: Discard all Lightning Energy attached to Luxray.

flavorText: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.

name: Mamoswine

attacks.name: Ice Fang
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Charge Through
attacks.text: You may do 60 damage plus 40 more damage and 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) If you do, Mamoswine does 40 damage to itself.

flavorText: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

name: Metagross

abilities.name: Magnetic Reversal
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with 1 of the Defending Pokémon. This power can't be used if Metagross is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Extra Comet Punch
attacks.text: During your next turn, Metagross's Extra Comet Punch attack's base damage is 100.

flavorText: Metang combined to form it. With four brains, it has the intelligence of a supercomputer.

name: Mewtwo

attacks.name: Hypnoblast
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

name: Politoed

abilities.name: Enthusiasm
abilities.text: If you have Poliwag, Poliwhirl, and Poliwrath in play, each of these Pokémon's attacks does 60 more damage to the Defending Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Frog Hop
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 40 more damage.

flavorText: It gathers groups of others as their leader. Its cries make Poliwag obey.

name: Probopass

abilities.name: Steel Coating
abilities.text: Any damage done to Probopass by your opponent's attacks is reduced by 10 for each Metal Energy attached to Probopass (after applying Weakness and Resistance). You can't reduce more than 20 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Metal Bomber
attacks.text: Choose a number of your opponent's Benched Pokémon up to the amount of Metal Energy attached to Probopass. This attack does 20 damage to each of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units call Mini-Noses.

name: Rayquaza

abilities.name: Speed Gain
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, search your discard pile for a basic Fire Energy card or a basic Lightning Energy card and attach it to Rayquaza. This power can't be used if Rayquaza is affected by a Special Condition or if you have another Rayquaza in play.

attacks.name: Sky Judgement
attacks.text: Discard all Energy attached to Rayquaza.

flavorText: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

name: Regigigas

abilities.name: Slow Start
abilities.text: Regigigas can't attack until your opponent has 3 or less Prize cards left.

attacks.name: Crush Grip
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack's base damage is 40 instead of 120.

flavorText: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

name: Spiritomb

abilities.name: Curse Breath
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Spiritomb from your hand onto your Bench, you may put 1 damage counter on all Pokémon that already have any damage counters on them (both yours and your opponent's). You can't use more than 1 Curse Breath Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Transfer Pain
attacks.text: Move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokémon to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

flavorText: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

name: Yanmega

attacks.name: Sonic Wave
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Pursue and Turn
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has 2 or more damage counters on it, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage and switch Yanmega with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.

name: Armaldo

abilities.name: Fossil Armor
abilities.text: If Armaldo would be damaged by an attack, prevent that attack's damage done to Armaldo if that damage is 60 or less.

attacks.name: Crush Claw
attacks.text: During your next turn, if an attack does damage to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: It went ashore after evolving. Its entire body is clad in a sturdy armor.

name: Azelf

abilities.name: Time Walk
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Azelf from your hand onto your Bench, you may look at all of your face-down Prize cards. If you do, you may choose 1 Pokémon you find there, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Then, choose 1 card in your hand and put it as a Prize card face down.

attacks.name: Lock Up
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

name: Bellossom

attacks.name: Parallel Gain
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Blend Pollen
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 20 more damage for each Vileplume and each Bellossom you have in play. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

name: Cradily

attacks.name: Drain Down
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you may switch 1 of the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 30 damage to the new Defending Pokémon. If the Defending Pokémon would be Knocked Out by this attack, you may remove all damage counters from Cradily.

attacks.name: Acid
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.

name: Crawdaunt

attacks.name: Gripthrow
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent returns the Defending Pokémon and all cards attached to it to his or her hand.

attacks.name: Prop-up Pinchers
attacks.text: If Crawdaunt has a Technical Machine card attached to it, this attack does 50 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokémon from its pond.

name: Delcatty

abilities.name: Attracting Body
abilities.text: If Delcatty is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Delcatty is Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, the Attacking Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Energy Assist
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.

name: Deoxys Attack Forme

abilities.name: Form Change
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for any Deoxys and switch it with Deoxys Attack Forme. (Any cards attached to Deoxys Attack Forme, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) If you do, put Deoxys Attack Forme on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward. You can't use more than 1 Form Change Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Psychic Boost
attacks.text: During your next turn, Deoxys's Psychic Boost attack's base damage is 20.

flavorText: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: Deoxys Defense Forme

abilities.name: Form Change
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for any Deoxys and switch it with Deoxys Defense Forme. (Any cards attached to Deoxys Defense Forme, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) If you do, put Deoxys Defense Forme on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward. You can't use more than 1 Form Change Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Psychic Defense
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of an attack, and any damage done to Deoxys by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: Deoxys Speed Forme

abilities.name: Form Change
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for any Deoxys and switch it with Deoxys Speed Forme. (Any cards attached to Deoxys Speed Forme, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) If you do, put Deoxys Speed Forme on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward. You can't use more than 1 Form Change Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Speed Shot
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

flavorText: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: Ditto

abilities.name: Ditto DNA
abilities.text: As long as Ditto is your Active Pokémon, its maximum HP is the same as your opponent's Active Pokémon. Ditto can use the attacks of that Pokémon as its own. (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.) If that Pokémon is no longer your opponent's Active Pokémon, choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon for Ditto to copy.

flavorText: It has the ability to reconstitute its entire cellular structure to transform into whatever it sees.

name: Forretress

abilities.name: Iron Shell
abilities.text: Whenever you attach a basic Energy card from your hand to Forretress (excluding effects of attacks), you may flip a coin. If tails, put 2 damage counters on each Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) (excluding any Forretress).

attacks.name: Explosion
attacks.text: Forretress does 40 damage to itself.

flavorText: It is encased in a steel shell. Its peering eyes are all that can be seen of its mysterious innards.

name: Groudon

attacks.name: Drought
attacks.text: Choose up to 2 basic Fighting Energy cards from your hand and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Major Earthquake
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fighting Energy attached to Groudon and this attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.

name: Heatran

abilities.name: Smelt
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Metal Energy attached to 1 of your Pokémon to Heatran. This power can't be used if Heatran is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Heavy Metal
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Metal Energy attached to Heatran. This attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Jirachi

attacks.name: One Desire
attacks.text: Search your deck for any 1 card. Shuffle your deck, then put that card on top of your deck.

attacks.name: Doom Desire
attacks.text: Discard all Energy attached to Jirachi. The Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out at the end of your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

name: Kyogre

attacks.name: Drizzle
attacks.text: Choose up to 2 basic Water Energy cards from your hand and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: High Tide
attacks.text: Discard 2 Water Energy attached to Kyogre. This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

name: Lopunny

abilities.name: Healing Tail
abilities.text: As long as Lopunny is your Active Pokémon, remove 1 damage counter from each of your Benched Pokémon between turns.

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw 3 cards.

attacks.name: Cross-Cut
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is an Evolved Pokémon, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

name: Mesprit

abilities.name: Psychic Bind
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Mesprit from your hand onto your Bench, you may use this power. Your opponent can't use any Poké-Powers on his or her Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Extrasensory
attacks.text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 20 damage plus 50 more damage.

flavorText: Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: Poliwrath

attacks.name: Focus Punch
attacks.text: If Poliwrath was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Submission
attacks.text: Poliwrath does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: With extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

name: Regice

abilities.name: Regi Move
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Discard 2 cards from your hand and choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon that isn't an Evolved Pokémon. Then, your opponent switches that Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon. This power can't be used if Regice is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Ice Reflect
attacks.text: If Regice was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Regigigas

abilities.name: Recover Mechanism
abilities.text: When you attach an Energy card from your hand to Regigigas, remove all Special Conditions from Regigigas.

attacks.name: Gigaton Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage and does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

name: Regirock

abilities.name: Regi Cycle
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have a Fighting Energy card in your discard pile, you may discard 2 cards from your hand. Then, attach a Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to Regirock. This power can't be used if Regirock is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Stone Edge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.

name: Registeel

abilities.name: Regi Heal
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard 2 cards from your hand. Then, remove 3 damage counters from Registeel. This power can't be used if Registeel is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Rotating Claws
attacks.text: You may discard an Energy card attached to Registeel. If you do, search your discard pile for an Energy card (excluding the one you discarded) and attach it to Registeel.

flavorText: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.

name: Shedinja

abilities.name: Resent
abilities.text: Once during your opponent's turn, if Shedinja would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, you may put 4 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon and each of the opponent's Pokémon that has the same name as the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Curse and Deceive
attacks.text: Put 3 damage counters on the Defending Pokémon. If Shedinja has any damage counters on it, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one's spirit.

name: Torkoal

abilities.name: White Smoke
abilities.text: As long as Torkoal is your Active Pokémon, prevent all effects, including damage, done to your Benched Pokémon by your opponent's attacks.

attacks.name: Black Soot
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned and Paralyzed.

flavorText: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

name: Unown [!]

abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Unown ! from your hand onto your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If tails, put 2 damage counters on 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage. If tails, Unown ! does 10 damage to itself, and this attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

flavorText: Shaped like an ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Uxie

abilities.name: Set Up
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Uxie from your hand onto your Bench, you may draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Psychic Restore
attacks.text: You may put Uxie and all cards attached to it on the bottom of your deck in any order.

flavorText: Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

name: Victreebel

attacks.name: Burning Scent
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned and Poisoned. Before applying these effects, you may switch 1 of the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. The new Defending Pokémon is now Burned and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Energy Dissolve
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon at the end of your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honeylike scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.

name: Vileplume

abilities.name: Energy Reaction
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you attach a Grass or Psychic Energy card from your hand to Vileplume (excluding effects of attacks or Poké-Powers), you may use this power. If you attach a Grass Energy card, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. If you attach a Psychic Energy card, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. This power can't be used if Vileplume is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Disturbing Pollen
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't play any Trainer, Supporter, or Stadium cards from his or her hand during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.

name: Anorith

attacks.name: Guard Claw
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Anorith by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: A Pokémon ancestor that was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with claws.

name: Camerupt

attacks.name: Eruption
