attacks.text: Each player discards the top of his or her deck. This attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage for each Energy card discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: Camerupt does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: It has volcanoes on its back. If magma builds up in its body, it shudders, then erupts violently.

name: Castform

abilities.name: Temperament
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for any Castform and switch it with Castform. (Any cards attached to Castform, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) If you do, put Castform on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward. You can't use more than 1 Temperament Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Weather Ball
attacks.text: If you have a Stadium card in play, remove 3 damage counters from Castform. If your opponent has a Stadium card in play, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage.

flavorText: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.

name: Castform Rain Form

abilities.name: Temperament
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for any Castform and switch it with Castform Rain Form. (Any cards attached to Castform Rain Form, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) Shuffle Castform Rain Form back into your deck. You can't use more than 1 Temperament Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Water Pulse
attacks.text: The defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.

name: Castform Snow-Cloud Form

abilities.name: Temperament
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for any Castform and switch it with Castform Snow-cloud Form. (Any cards attached to Castform Snow-cloud Form, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) Shuffle Castform Snow-cloud Form back into your deck. You can't use more than 1 Temperament Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Hail
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.

name: Castform Sunny Form

abilities.name: Temperament
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for any Castform and switch it with Castform Sunny Form. (Any cards attached to Castform Sunny Form, damage counters, Special Conditions, and effects on it are now on the new Pokémon.) Shuffle Castform Sunny Form back into your deck. You can't use more than 1 Temperament Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to Castform Sunny Form.

flavorText: Its appearance changes with the weather. Recently, its molecules were found to be just like water.

name: Dragonair

attacks.name: Wrap
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Rising Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.

name: Drifblim

attacks.name: Expand
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Drifblim by attacks is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It's drowzy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

name: Exeggutor

attacks.name: Psychic Strategy
attacks.text: Each player counts the number of cards in his or her opponent's hand. Each player shuffles his or her hand into his or her deck. Then, each player draws a number of cards up to the number of cards his or her opponent had. (You draw your cards first.)

attacks.name: Super Eggsplosion
attacks.text: Discard as many Energy cards as you like attached to your Pokémon. For each Energy card you discarded, flip a coin. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It is called "The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

name: Gliscor

attacks.name: Poison Jab
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Sharp Tail
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 40 more damage.

flavorText: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

name: Grumpig

attacks.name: Magical Step
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused. Put 6 damage counters instead of 3 on the Confused Pokémon.

attacks.name: Grind
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to Grumpig.

flavorText: It uses black pearls to amplify its psycho-power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

name: Houndoom

abilities.name: Revenge Fang
abilities.text: If you have less Benched Pokémon than your opponent, each of Houndoom's attacks does 40 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Burning Sensation
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Bright Flame
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard 2 Fire Energy attached to Houndoom.

flavorText: Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.

name: Lanturn

attacks.name: Rushing Water
attacks.text: Move an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon to another of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Lanturn's light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed "The Deep-Sea Star."

name: Lanturn

attacks.name: Energy Split
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon that has any Energy cards attached to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Aqua Bolt
attacks.text: Does 60 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Lanturn.

flavorText: Lanturn's light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed "The Deep-Sea Star."

name: Ledian

attacks.name: Comet Punch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Baton Pass
attacks.text: You may switch Ledian with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, move as many Energy cards attached to Ledian as you like to the new Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.

name: Lucario

attacks.name: Focus Blast
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Spike Lariat
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

name: Luxio

attacks.name: Spark
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Thunderous Claw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard all Lightning Energy attached to Luxio.

flavorText: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.

name: Marowak

attacks.name: Heavy Bone
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Marowak can't use Heavy Bone during your next turn.

attacks.name: Bone Rush
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: From its birth, this savage Pokémon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.

name: Metang

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Metang during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its steel body won't be scratched if it collides with a jet.

name: Metang

attacks.name: Psyshock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Bullet Punch
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its steel body won't be scratched if it collides with a jet.

name: Mightyena

attacks.name: Bite On
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon isn't an Evolved Pokémon, that Pokémon can't attack, retreat, or use any Poké-Powers during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Harass
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the number of Pokémon you have in play.

flavorText: It chases down prey in a pack. It will never disobey the commands of a skilled Trainer.

name: Ninjask

abilities.name: Cast-off Shell
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play Ninjask from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon and if your Bench isn't full, you may put Shedinja onto your Bench as a Basic Pokémon from your hand or your discard pile.

attacks.name: Chip Off
attacks.text: If your opponent has 6 or more cards in his or her hand, discard a number of cards without looking until your opponent has 5 cards left in his or her hand.

flavorText: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.

name: Persian

attacks.name: Feint Attack
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Fasten Claws
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: A very haughty Pokémon. Among fans, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.

name: Piloswine

attacks.name: Charge Dash
attacks.text: You may do 30 damage plus 30 more damage. If you do, Piloswine does 30 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Icy Wind
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: Its shaggy coat makes it unable to see. It checks surroundings with its sensitive nose instead.

name: Seadra

attacks.name: Aqua Pump
attacks.text: You may discard up to 2 Water Energy cards from your hand. If you do, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card you discarded.

flavorText: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional medicine ingredients.

name: Starmie

attacks.name: Star Boomerang
attacks.text: You may return Starmie and all cards attached to it to your hand.

attacks.name: Core Flash
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon that has any Poké-Powers or Poké-Bodies. This attack does 50 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: At the center of its body is a red core, which sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.

name: Swalot

attacks.name: Swallow Up
attacks.text: Before doing damage, count the remaining HP of the Defending Pokémon and Swalot. If the Defending Pokémon has fewer remaining HP than Swalot's, this attack does 80 damage instead.

attacks.name: Gunk Shot
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.

name: Swellow

abilities.name: Big Wing
abilities.text: If Swellow has no Energy attached to it, Swellow's Retreat Cost is 0.

attacks.name: Mach Descent
attacks.text: If Swellow was on your Bench this turn, this attack's base damage is 60 instead of 30.

flavorText: It circles the sky in search of prey. When it spots one, it dive steeply to catch the prey.

name: Tauros

attacks.name: Herd Charge
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Tauros you have in play. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Thrash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage. If tails, Tauros does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: Once it takes aim at its foe, it makes a headlong charge. It is famous for its violent nature.

name: Tentacruel

attacks.name: Tentacle Strike
attacks.text: Search your opponent's discard pile for up to 2 Energy cards and attach them to any of your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like. For each Energy card attached in this way, this attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Dangerous Poison
attacks.text: If Tentacruel has less Energy attached to it than the Defending Pokémon, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

flavorText: With 80 tentacles for ensnaring victims, it prevents escape until the prey is weakened by poison.

name: Unown [J]

abilities.name: JUNK
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Unown J from your hand onto your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for a Trainer card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Remove the Special Condition Asleep from the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: Shaped like an ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Unown [R]

abilities.name: RETIRE
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if Unown R is on your Bench, you may discard Unown R and all cards attached to it. (This doesn't count as a Knocked Out Pokémon.) Then, draw a card.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Move any number of basic Energy cards attached to your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

flavorText: Shaped like an ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Unown [U]

abilities.name: UNSEEN
abilities.text: As long as Unown U is on your Bench, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done by your opponent's Pokémon to any Unown on your Bench.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Search your deck for any 1 card and discard it. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: Shaped like an ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Unown [V]

abilities.name: VACATION
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 2 damage counters from each of your Pokémon. If you do, your turn ends. This power can't be used if Unown V is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Shaped like an ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Unown [W]

abilities.name: WALL
abilities.text: As long as Unown W is your Active Pokémon, any damage done to your Pokémon by an opponent's attack is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: Shaped like an ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Unown [Y]

abilities.name: YAWN
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown Y is on your Bench, you may remove 1 damage counter from 1 of your Active Unown and that Unown is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Trainer cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

flavorText: Shaped like an ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Unown [?]

abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown ? is on your Bench, you may choose a Pokémon in your hand and put it face down. Your opponent guesses a type of that Pokémon. Reveal that card. If your opponent guessed wrong, draw a card. Then, put that card back into your hand.

attacks.name: Hidden Power
attacks.text: Discard up to 2 cards from your hand. For each card you discarded, draw a card.

flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Beldum

abilities.name: Metal Chain
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you attach a Metal Energy card from your hand to Beldum (excluding effects of attacks or Poké-Powers), you may search your deck for Beldum and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Beldum is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: Beldum does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.

name: Beldum

attacks.name: Allure
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: It converses with others by using magnetic pulses. In a swarm, they move in perfect unison.

name: Bellsprout

attacks.name: Vine Bind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't use any Poké-Powers during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Careless Tackle
attacks.text: Bellsprout does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.

name: Buneary

attacks.name: Rest
attacks.text: Remove all Special Conditions and 4 damage counters from Buneary. Buneary is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Double Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.

name: Chinchou

attacks.name: Supersonic
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.

name: Chinchou

attacks.name: Aqua Spark
attacks.text: If Chinchou has any Water Energy attached to it, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.

name: Corphish

attacks.name: Knock Off
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

flavorText: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.

name: Cubone

attacks.name: Bonemerang
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.

name: Dratini

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It is called the "Mirage Pokémon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

name: Drifloon

attacks.name: Mind Bend
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.

name: Exeggcute

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 in any combination of Grass Basic Pokémon and Psychic Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Hypnosis
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.

name: Gligar

attacks.name: Light Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Jump On
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: It sails on the winds with its limbs extended to strike from the sky. It aims for the prey's face.

name: Gligar

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It sails on the winds with its limbs extended to strike from the sky. It aims for the prey's face.

name: Gloom

attacks.name: Sleep Powder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Frustration
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon that doesn't have any damage counters on it. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

name: Gloom

attacks.name: Space Out
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters from Gloom. Gloom is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Stinky Nectar
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

flavorText: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

name: Gulpin

attacks.name: Amnesia
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Gastro Acid
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Almost all its body is its stomach. Its harsh digestive juices quickly dissolve anything it swallows.

name: Hitmonchan

attacks.name: Counter Punch
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if Hitmonchan is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Hitmonchan is Knocked Out), put 4 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Gut Strike
attacks.text: If Tyrogue is anywhere under Hitmonchan, this attack's base damage is 60 instead of 30.

flavorText: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.

name: Hitmonlee

attacks.name: Gut Kick
attacks.text: If Tyrogue is anywhere under Hitmonlee, you may do 30 damage to any 1 Benched Pokémon instead. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Its legs can stretch double. First-time foes are startled by its extensible reach.

name: Hitmontop

attacks.name: Triple Kick
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Gut Spin
attacks.text: If Tyrogue is anywhere under Hitmontop, you may switch Hitmontop with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by ten.

name: Horsea

attacks.name: Smokescreen
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Reverse Thrust
attacks.text: Switch Horsea with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

name: Houndour

attacks.name: Roar
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It conveys its feelings using different cries. It works in a pack to cleverly take down prey.

name: Ledyba

attacks.name: Supersonic
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Double-edge
attacks.text: Ledyba does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It is so timid, it can't move if it isn't with a swarm of others. It conveys its feelings with scent.

name: Lileep

attacks.name: Astonish
attacks.text: Choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking. Look at that card you chose, then have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Absorb
attacks.text: Remove 2 damage counters from Lileep.

flavorText: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.

name: Meowth

attacks.name: Pay Day
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, draw a card.

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.

name: Misdreavus

attacks.name: Show Off
attacks.text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Payback
attacks.text: If your opponent has only 1 Prize card left, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: It loves to sneak up on people late at night, then startle them with its shrieklike cry.

name: Nincada

attacks.name: Big Bite
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.

name: Nosepass

attacks.name: Nose Poke
attacks.text: If Probopass is on your Bench, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: Its nose is a magnet. As a result, this Pokémon always keeps its face pointing north.

name: Numel

attacks.name: Singe
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.

name: Oddish

attacks.name: Stun Spore
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Blot
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from Oddish.

flavorText: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.

name: Oddish

attacks.name: Poisonpowder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.

name: Pineco

attacks.name: Selfdestruct
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage to each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Pineco does 50 damage to itself.

flavorText: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

name: Poliwag

attacks.name: Twiddle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.

name: Poliwhirl

attacks.name: Bubblebeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.

name: Poochyena

attacks.name: Corner
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Ambush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

name: Riolu
flavorText: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

name: Shinx

attacks.name: Recharge
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card attach it to Shinx. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Double Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

name: Skitty

attacks.name: Growl
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: It can't stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.

name: Sneasel

attacks.name: Rob
attacks.text: Look at your opponent's hand. If your opponent has any Pokémon Tool or Technical Machine cards in his or her hand, put those cards on top of his or her deck. Your opponent shuffles his or her deck afterward.

flavorText: It feeds on eggs stolen from nests. Its sharply hooked claws rip vulnerable spots on prey.

name: Spoink

attacks.name: Psybeam
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Bounce
attacks.text: You may switch Spoink with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It bounces constantly, using its tail like a spring. The shock of bouncing keeps its heart beating.

name: Staryu

attacks.name: Recover
attacks.text: Discard an Energy attached to Staryu and remove 3 damage counters from Staryu.

flavorText: Its body is virtually composed of water. It shoots strange beams from its crystal-like eyes.

name: Swinub

attacks.name: Sniff Out
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, put any 1 card from your discard pile into your hand.

flavorText: It loves eating mushrooms that grow under dead grass. It also finds hot springs while foraging.

name: Taillow

attacks.name: Focus Energy
attacks.text: During your next turn, Taillow's Peck attack's base damage is 30.

flavorText: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.

name: Tentacool

attacks.name: Crystal Barrier
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Tentacool during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Mysterious Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

flavorText: Its body is virtually composed of water. It shoots strange beams from its crystal-like eyes.

name: Tyrogue

abilities.name: Baby Evolution
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put Hitmonlee, Hitmonchan, or Hitmontop from your hand onto Tyrogue (this counts as evolving Tyrogue) and remove all damage counters from Tyrogue.

attacks.name: Gut Blow
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is an Evolved Pokémon, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage and Tyrogue does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.

name: Weepinbell

attacks.name: Poisonpowder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: A Pokémon that appears to be a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.

name: Yanma

attacks.name: U-turn
attacks.text: Switch Yanma with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Yanma during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won't miss prey—even those behind it.

name: Bubble Coat
rules: Attach Bubble Coat to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't already have a Pokémon Tool attached to it. If that Pokémon is Knocked Out, discard this card.
As long as Bubble Coat is attached to a Pokémon, that Pokémon has no Weakness. If that Pokémon is damaged by an opponent's attack, discard this card at the end of the turn.

name: Buck's Training
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Draw 2 cards. As long as Buck's Training is next to your Active Pokémon, each of your Active Pokémon's attacks does 10 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Cynthia's Feelings
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 4 cards. If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn, draw 4 more cards.

name: Energy Pickup
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for a basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Poké Radar
rules: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck, choose as many Pokémon as you like, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Put the other cards back on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Snowpoint Temple
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play. If another card with the same name is in play, you can't play this card.
Each Pokémon that isn't an Evolved Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) gets +20 HP.

name: Stark Mountain
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play. If another card with the same name is in play, you can't play this card.
Once during each player's turn, that player may choose a Fire or Fighting Energy attached to 1 of his or her Pokémon and move that Energy to 1 of his or her Pokémon.

name: Technical Machine TS-1
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Pokémon in play. That Pokémon may use this card's attack instead of its own.

attacks.name: Evoluter
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of your Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon. (This counts as evolving that Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Technical Machine TS-2
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Pokémon in play. That Pokémon may use this card's attack instead of its own.

attacks.name: Devoluter
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Evolved Pokémon (excluding Pokémon LV.X). Remove the highest Stage Evolution card from that Pokémon and put that card back into your opponent's hand.

name: Claw Fossil
rules: Play Claw Fossil as if it were a Colorless Basic Pokémon. (Claw Fossil counts as a Trainer card as well, but if Claw Fossil is Knocked Out, this counts as a Knocked Out Pokémon.) Claw Fossil can't be affected by any Special Conditions and can't retreat. At any time during your turn before your attack, you may discard Claw Fossil from play. (This doesn't count as a Knocked Out Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Jagged Stone
abilities.text: If Claw Fossil is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Claw Fossil is Knocked Out), put 1 damage counter on the Attacking Pokémon.

name: Root Fossil
rules: Play Root Fossil as if it were a Colorless Basic Pokémon. (Root Fossil counts as a Trainer card as well, but if Root Fossil is Knocked Out, this counts as a Knocked Out Pokémon.) Root Fossil can't be affected by any Special Conditions and can't retreat. At any time during your turn before your attack, you may discard Root Fossil from play. (This doesn't count as a Knocked Out Pokémon.)

abilities.name: Spongy Stone
abilities.text: At any time between turns, remove 1 damage counter from Root Fossil.

name: Azelf LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Azelf. Azelf LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Psychic Aura
abilities.text: Each of your Psychic Pokémon has no Weakness.

attacks.name: Deep Balance
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. Put 1 damage counter on that Pokémon for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Gliscor LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Gliscor. Gliscor LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Shoot Poison

attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Mouth Pump
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

name: Gastly

attacks.name: Pitch-Dark
attacks.text: You opponent can't play any Trainer cards from his or her hand during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Trick Gas
attacks.text: You may switch Gastly with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: This Pokémon's body is 95% made up of gases, which are blown away by strong gusts of wind.

name: Larvitar

attacks.name: Rock Slide
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: A Pokémon that eats soil. Once it has eaten a large mountain, it goes to sleep so it can grow.

name: Machop

attacks.name: Knock Back
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It hefts a Graveler repeatedly to strengthen its entire body. It uses every type of martial arts.

name: Magikarp

attacks.name: Sea Spray
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, draw a card.

flavorText: It is said to be the world's weakest Pokémon. No one knows why it has managed to survive.

name: Magnemite
rules: Magnet: Magnemite's Retreat Cost is Colorless less for each Magnemite on your Bench.

attacks.name: Magnetic Bomb
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage. If tails, Magnemite does 10 damage to itself.

name: Magnemite

attacks.name: Random Spark
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: The units at its sides generate electromagnetic waves that keep it airborne. It feeds on electricity.

name: Misdreavus

attacks.name: Lullaby
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Nightmare Feast
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon is Asleep, this attack does 50 damage and remove 5 damage counters from Misdreavus. If the Defending Pokémon is not Asleep, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It loves to sneak up on people late at night, then startle them with its shrieklike cry.

name: Onix

attacks.name: Harden
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if Onix would be damaged by an attack, prevent that attack's damage done to Onix if that damage is 40 or less.

attacks.name: Bind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: When it travels underground, it causes rumbling and tremors. It can move at 50 mph.

name: Pikachu

attacks.name: Speed Bolt
attacks.text: If Pikachu evolved from Pichu during this turn, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Pikachu during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: It lives in forests with others. It stores electricity in the pouches on its cheeks.

name: Ponyta

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Ponyta during your opponent's next turn.

flavorText: About an hour after birth, its fiery mane and tail grow out, giving it an impressive appearance.

name: Roselia

attacks.name: Petal Spikes
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned. If Budew is anywhere under Roselia, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

flavorText: Roselia raised on clean drinking water are known to grow vividly colored flowers.

name: Skorupi

attacks.name: Stalk
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Dangerous Claw
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.

name: Snover

attacks.name: Hide
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Snover during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Powder Snow
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

name: Starly

attacks.name: Sand Attack
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Double Stab
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.

name: Stunky

attacks.name: Gnaw and Run
attacks.text: Switch Stunky with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Double Scratch
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

name: Swinub

attacks.name: Freezing Breath
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Swinub does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It loves eating mushrooms that grow under dead grass. It also finds hot springs while foraging.

name: Tangela

attacks.name: Ingrain
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, search your deck for a Grass Energy card and attach it to Tangela. Shuffle your deck afterward. If you do, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Tangela during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Tickle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It is shrouded by blue vines. No one has seen the face hidden behind this growth of vines.

name: Treecko

attacks.name: Call for Friends
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Poison Breath
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

name: Voltorb

attacks.name: Screech
attacks.text: If an attack does damage to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 20 more damage to that Pokémon until the end of your next turn.

attacks.name: Double Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

flavorText: It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.

name: Voltorb

attacks.name: Outlet
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Bouncing Ball
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Voltorb does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on touch.

name: Conductive Quarry
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play. If another card with the same name is in play, you can't play this card.

Once during each player's turn, the player may flip a coin. If heads, that player searches his or her discard pile for a Lightning or Metal Energy card, shows it to the opponent, and puts it into his or her hand.

name: Energy Link
rules: Attach Energy Link to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't already have a Pokémon Tool attached to it. If that Pokémon is Knocked Out, discard this card.

As long as Energy Link is attached to a Pokémon, you may move an Energy card attached to that Pokémon to another of your Pokémon that has Energy Link attached to it. You may use this effect as often as you like during your turn.

name: Energy Switch
rules: Move a basic Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

name: Great Ball
rules: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Luxury Ball
rules: Search your deck for a Pokémon (excluding Pokémon LV.X), show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. If any Luxury Ball is in your discard pile, you can't play this card.

name: Marley's Request
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokémon. When your turn ends, discard this card.

Search your discard pile for 2 different Trainer, Supporter, or Stadium cards, show them to your opponent, and your opponent chooses 1 of them. Put that card into your hand, and discard the other card. (If all Trainer, Supporter, and Stadium cards in your discard pile have the same name, choose 1 of them. Show that card to your opponent and put it into your hand.)

name: Poké Blower +
rules: You may play 2 Poké Blower + at the same time. If you play 1 Poké Blower +, flip a coin. If heads, put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If you play 2 Poké Blower +, choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and switch it with 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Poké Drawer +
rules: You may play 2 Poké Drawer + at the same time. If you play 1 Poké Drawer +, draw a card. If you play 2 Poké Drawer +, search your deck for up to 2 cards, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Poké Healer +
rules: You may play 2 Poké Healer + at the same time. If you play 1 Poké Healer +, remove 1 damage counter and a Special Condition from 1 of your Active Pokémon. If you play 2 Poké Healer +, remove 8 damage counters and all Special Conditions from 1 of your Active Pokémon.

name: Premier Ball
rules: Search your deck or your discard pile for a Pokémon LV.X, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. If you search your deck, shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Potion
rules: Remove 2 damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon (remove 1 damage counter if that Pokémon has only 1).

name: Switch
rules: Switch 1 of your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Cyclone Energy
rules: Cyclone Energy provides Colorless Energy. When you attach this card from your hand to your Active Pokémon, switch 1 of the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. Your opponent chooses the Benched Pokémon to switch.

name: Warp Energy
rules: Warp Energy provides Colorless Energy. When you attach this card from your hand to your Active Pokémon, switch that Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Dusknoir LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Dusknoir. Dusknoir LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Ectoplasm
abilities.text: If Dusknoir is your Active Pokémon and would be Knocked Out by damage from your opponent's attack, you may discard all cards attached to Dusknoir LV.X and put Dusknoir LV.X as a Stadium card into play instead of discarding it. This counts as Dusknoir being Knocked Out and your opponent takes a Prize card. As long as you have Dusknoir LV.X as a Stadium card in play, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon between turns. If another Stadium card comes into play or Dusknoir LV.X is discarded by the effects of any attacks, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, Trainer, or Supporter cards, return Dusknoir LV.X to your hand.

name: Heatran LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Heatran. Heatran LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Heat Metal
abilities.text: Your opponent can't remove the Special Condition Burned by evolving or devolving his or her Burned Pokémon. (This also includes putting a Pokémon Level-Up card onto the Burned Pokémon.) Whenever your opponent flips a coin for the Special Condition Burned between turns, treat it as tails.

abilities.name: Heat Wave
abilities.text: Once at the end of your turn, if Heatran is on your Bench, you may use this power. If you discarded basic Energy cards attached to your Fire or Metal Active Pokémon by using that Pokémon's attack this turn, attach up to 2 of those Energy cards to that Pokémon.

name: Machamp LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Machamp. Machamp LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: No Guard
abilities.text: As long as Machamp is your Active Pokémon, each of Machamp's attacks does 60 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance) and any damage done to Machamp by your opponent's Pokémon is increased by 60 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Strong-Willed
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if Machamp would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, Machamp is not Knocked Out and its remaining HP becomes 10 instead.

name: Raichu LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Raichu. Raichu LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Link Lightning
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Raichu LV.X onto Raichu and use Voltage Shoot, you may use another attack of Raichu afterward. This power can't be used if Raichu is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Voltage Shoot
attacks.text: Discard 2 Lightning Energy cards from your hand and choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 80 to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Regigigas LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Regigigas. Regigigas LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Sacrifice
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose 1 of your Pokémon in play and that Pokémon is Knocked Out. Then, search your discard pile for up to 2 basic Energy cards, attach them to Regigigas, and remove 8 damage counters from Regigigas. This power can't be used if Regigigas is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Giga Blaster
attacks.text: Discard the top card from your opponent's deck. Then, choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it. Regigigas can't use Giga Blaster during your next turn.

name: Charmander

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to Charmander.

flavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

name: Charmeleon

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy attached to Charmeleon.

flavorText: It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.

name: Charizard

abilities.name: Energy Burn
abilities.text: All Energy attached to Charizard are Fire Energy instead of their usual type.

attacks.name: Fire Spin
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy attached to Charizard.

flavorText: Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.

abilities.name: Unburden
abilities.text: If Drifloon has a Pokémon Tool card attached to it, Drifloon's Retreat Cost is ColorlessColorless more.

attacks.name: Big Explosion
attacks.text: Drifloon does 50 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Counting Song
attacks.text: Put up to 3 damage counters on Duskull. Then, put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Night Bind
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't attach any Energy cards from his or her hand to the Active Pokémon during his or her next turn.

attacks.name: Fastball
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Charge Beam
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to Voltorb.

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Turtwig
flavorText: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.

name: Chimchar

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard a Fire Energy attached to Chimchar.

flavorText: It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.

name: Piplup

attacks.name: Water Splash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

name: Pachirisu

attacks.name: Minor Errand-Running
attacks.text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Thunder Jolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Pachirisu does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

name: Tropical Wind
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, remove 2 damage counters from each Active Pokémon (remove 1 damage counter if a Pokémon has only 1). If tails, each Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Buneary

attacks.name: Jump Kick
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.

name: Cranidos

attacks.name: Steamroll
attacks.text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its skull is as hard as iron.

name: Shieldon

attacks.name: Hard Face
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Shieldon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Shield Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage.

flavorText: A Pokémon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.

name: Torterra LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Torterra. Torterra LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Forest Murmurs
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have more Prize cards left than your opponent, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and switch it with 1 of the Defending Pokémon. This power can't be used if Torterra is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Vigorous Dash
attacks.text: Does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Torterra does 30 damage to itself.

name: Infernape LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Infernape. Infernape LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Burning Head
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck, choose 1 of them, and put it into your hand. Discard the other 2 cards. This power can't be used if Infernape is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Flare Up
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for 8 Fire Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and shuffle them into your deck. (This attack does nothing if you don't have 8 Fire Energy cards in your discard pile.)

name: Empoleon LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Empoleon. Empoleon LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Supreme Command
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose up to 2 cards from your opponent's hand without looking and put them face down next to the Defending Pokémon. (These cards are not in play or in your opponent's hand.) At the end of your opponent's next turn, return those cards to your opponent's hand. This power can't be used if Empoleon is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hydro Impact
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage to that Pokémon (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Empoleon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Lucario LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Lucario. Lucario LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Stance
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Lucario LV.X from your hand onto your Active Lucario, you may use this power. Prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Lucario during your opponent's next turn. (If Lucario is no longer your Active Pokémon, this effect ends.)

attacks.name: Close Combat
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Lucario by attacks is increased by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Buizel

attacks.name: Splash About
attacks.text: If Buizel has less Energy attached to it than the Defending Pokémon, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.

name: Chatot

attacks.name: Me First
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Tone-Deaf
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: Shinx

attacks.name: Spark
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

name: Pikachu

abilities.name: Electro Recycle
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Pichu is anywhere under Pikachu, you may search your discard pile for a Lightning Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. This power can't be used if Pikachu is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: BikaBika
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage.

flavorText: It lives in forests with others. It stores electricity in the pouches on its cheeks.

name: Dialga LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Dialga. Dialga LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Time Skip
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may have your opponent flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, your turn ends. If both of them are tails, after your opponent draws a card at the beginning of his or her next turn, his or her turn ends. This power can't be used if Dialga is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Metal Flash
attacks.text: During your next turn, Dialga can't use Metal Flash.

name: Palkia LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Palkia. Palkia LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Restructure
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may have your opponent switch 1 of your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. Then, you switch 1 of the Defending Pokémon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. This power can't be used if Palkia is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Hydro Reflect
attacks.text: You may move all Energy cards attached to Palkia to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like. (Ignore this effect if you don't have any Benched Pokémon.)

name: Darkrai LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Darkrai. Darkrai LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Dark Shadow
abilities.text: Each basic Darkness Energy card attached to your Darkness Pokémon now has the effect "If the Pokémon Darkness Energy is attached to attacks, the attack does 10 more damage to the Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance)." You can't use more than 1 Dark Shadow Poké-Body each turn.

attacks.name: Endless Darkness
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep. Flip 2 coins instead of 1 between turns. If either of them is tails, the Defending Pokémon is still Asleep. If both of them are tails, the Defending Pokémon is Knocked Out.

name: Magmortar

attacks.name: Smoke Bomb
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Flame Drum
attacks.text: If Magby isn't anywhere under Magmortar, discard 2 Energy cards from your hand. (If you can't discard 2 Energy cards from your hand, this attack does nothing.)

flavorText: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

name: Raichu

attacks.name: Electromagnetic Induction
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Lightning Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Explosive Thunder
attacks.text: Discard all basic Lightning Energy cards attached to Raichu. This attack does 30 damage times the number of Lightning Energy cards you discarded.

flavorText: It turns aggressive if it has too much electricity in its body. It discharges power through its tail.

name: Mime Jr.

abilities.name: Baby Evolution
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put Mr. Mime from your hand onto Mime Jr. (this counts as evolving Mime Jr.) and remove all damage counters from Mime Jr.

attacks.name: Mime
attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a number of cards equal to the number of cards in your opponent's hand.

flavorText: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

name: Glameow

attacks.name: Charm
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Pose
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness if very popular among some.

name: Darkrai
rules: Enigma Berry: If Darkrai is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Fighting Pokémon, remove 4 damage counters at the end of that turn.

attacks.name: Spacial Rend
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. If there is any Stadium card in play, discard it.

attacks.name: Roar of Time
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for 3 Pokémon, show them to your opponent, and put them on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward. (If you don't have 3 Pokémon in your discard pile, this attack does nothing.)

name: Tropical Wind
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, remove 2 damage counters from each Active Pokémon (remove 1 damage counter if a Pokémon has only 1). If tails, each Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Dialga

attacks.name: Time Bellow
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Flash Cannon
attacks.text: You may return all Energy cards attached to Dialga to your hand. If you do, remove the highest Stage Evolution card from the Defending Pokémon and shuffle that card into your opponent's deck.

flavorText: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

name: Palkia

attacks.name: Spacial Rend
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. If there is any Stadium card in play, discard it.

attacks.name: Transback
attacks.text: You may flip a coin. If heads, discard all Energy attached to Palkia and put the Defending Pokémon and all cards attached to it on top of your opponent's deck. Your opponent shuffles his or her deck afterward.

flavorText: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

name: Mewtwo LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Mewtwo. Mewtwo LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Psybarrier
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Mewtwo by your opponent's Pokémon that isn't an Evolved Pokémon.

attacks.name: Giga Burn
attacks.text: Discard all Energy attached to Mewtwo.

name: Rhyperior LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Rhyperior. Rhyperior LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

attacks.name: Hard Crush
attacks.text: Discard the top 5 cards from your deck. This attack does 50 damage for each Energy card you discarded.

attacks.name: Upthrow
attacks.text: Search your discard pile for all Fighting Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and shuffle them into your deck.

name: Regigigas LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Regigigas. Regigigas LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Sacrifice

name: Apricorn Forest
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.

Once during each player's turn (before attacking), if that player's Bench isn't full, that player flips a coin. If heads, that player shows his or her opponent a basic Energy card from his or her hand. Then, that player searches his or her deck for a Basic Pokémon card of the same type (color) as the revealed Energy card and puts it onto his or her Bench. The player shuffles his or her deck afterward.
